6503 namespace {
6504 
6505  /// Visitor used to search for information about a header file.
6506  class HeaderFileInfoVisitor {
6507  FileEntryRef FE;
6508  std::optional<HeaderFileInfo> HFI;
6509 
6510  public:
6511  explicit HeaderFileInfoVisitor(FileEntryRef FE) : FE(FE) {}
6512 
6513  bool operator()(ModuleFile &M) {
6514  HeaderFileInfoLookupTable *Table
6515  = static_cast<HeaderFileInfoLookupTable *>(M.HeaderFileInfoTable);
6516  if (!Table)
6517  return false;
6518 
6519  // Look in the on-disk hash table for an entry for this file name.
6520  HeaderFileInfoLookupTable::iterator Pos = Table->find(FE);
6521  if (Pos == Table->end())
6522  return false;
6523 
6524  HFI = *Pos;
6525  return true;
6526  }
6527 
6528  std::optional<HeaderFileInfo> getHeaderFileInfo() const { return HFI; }
6529  };
6530 
6531 } // namespace
6532 
6533 HeaderFileInfo ASTReader::GetHeaderFileInfo(FileEntryRef FE) {
6534  HeaderFileInfoVisitor Visitor(FE);
6535  ModuleMgr.visit(Visitor);
6536  if (std::optional<HeaderFileInfo> HFI = Visitor.getHeaderFileInfo())
6537  return *HFI;
6538 
6539  return HeaderFileInfo();
6540 }
6541 
6542 void ASTReader::ReadPragmaDiagnosticMappings(DiagnosticsEngine &Diag) {
6543  using DiagState = DiagnosticsEngine::DiagState;
6544  SmallVector<DiagState *, 32> DiagStates;
6545 
6546  for (ModuleFile &F : ModuleMgr) {
6547  unsigned Idx = 0;
6548  auto &Record = F.PragmaDiagMappings;
6549  if (Record.empty())
6550  continue;
6551 
6552  DiagStates.clear();
6553 
6554  auto ReadDiagState = [&](const DiagState &BasedOn,
6555  bool IncludeNonPragmaStates) {
6556  unsigned BackrefID = Record[Idx++];
6557  if (BackrefID != 0)
6558  return DiagStates[BackrefID - 1];
6559 
6560  // A new DiagState was created here.
6561  Diag.DiagStates.push_back(BasedOn);
6562  DiagState *NewState = &Diag.DiagStates.back();
6563  DiagStates.push_back(NewState);
6564  unsigned Size = Record[Idx++];
6565  assert(Idx + Size * 2 <= Record.size() &&
6566  "Invalid data, not enough diag/map pairs");
6567  while (Size--) {
6568  unsigned DiagID = Record[Idx++];
6569  DiagnosticMapping NewMapping =
6570  DiagnosticMapping::deserialize(Record[Idx++]);
6571  if (!NewMapping.isPragma() && !IncludeNonPragmaStates)
6572  continue;
6573 
6574  DiagnosticMapping &Mapping = NewState->getOrAddMapping(DiagID);
6575 
6576  // If this mapping was specified as a warning but the severity was
6577  // upgraded due to diagnostic settings, simulate the current diagnostic
6578  // settings (and use a warning).
6579  if (NewMapping.wasUpgradedFromWarning() && !Mapping.isErrorOrFatal()) {
6580  NewMapping.setSeverity(diag::Severity::Warning);
6581  NewMapping.setUpgradedFromWarning(false);
6582  }
6583 
6584  Mapping = NewMapping;
6585  }
6586  return NewState;
6587  };
6588 
6589  // Read the first state.
6590  DiagState *FirstState;
6591  if (F.Kind == MK_ImplicitModule) {
6592  // Implicitly-built modules are reused with different diagnostic
6593  // settings. Use the initial diagnostic state from Diag to simulate this
6594  // compilation's diagnostic settings.
6595  FirstState = Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.FirstDiagState;
6596  DiagStates.push_back(FirstState);
6597 
6598  // Skip the initial diagnostic state from the serialized module.
6599  assert(Record[1] == 0 &&
6600  "Invalid data, unexpected backref in initial state");
6601  Idx = 3 + Record[2] * 2;
6602  assert(Idx < Record.size() &&
6603  "Invalid data, not enough state change pairs in initial state");
6604  } else if (F.isModule()) {
6605  // For an explicit module, preserve the flags from the module build
6606  // command line (-w, -Weverything, -Werror, ...) along with any explicit
6607  // -Wblah flags.
6608  unsigned Flags = Record[Idx++];
6609  DiagState Initial;
6610  Initial.SuppressSystemWarnings = Flags & 1; Flags >>= 1;
6611  Initial.ErrorsAsFatal = Flags & 1; Flags >>= 1;
6612  Initial.WarningsAsErrors = Flags & 1; Flags >>= 1;
6613  Initial.EnableAllWarnings = Flags & 1; Flags >>= 1;
6614  Initial.IgnoreAllWarnings = Flags & 1; Flags >>= 1;
6615  Initial.ExtBehavior = (diag::Severity)Flags;
6616  FirstState = ReadDiagState(Initial, true);
6617 
6618  assert(F.OriginalSourceFileID.isValid());
6619 
6620  // Set up the root buffer of the module to start with the initial
6621  // diagnostic state of the module itself, to cover files that contain no
6622  // explicit transitions (for which we did not serialize anything).
6623  Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.Files[F.OriginalSourceFileID]
6624  .StateTransitions.push_back({FirstState, 0});
6625  } else {
6626  // For prefix ASTs, start with whatever the user configured on the
6627  // command line.
6628  Idx++; // Skip flags.
6629  FirstState = ReadDiagState(*Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.CurDiagState, false);
6630  }
6631 
6632  // Read the state transitions.
6633  unsigned NumLocations = Record[Idx++];
6634  while (NumLocations--) {
6635  assert(Idx < Record.size() &&
6636  "Invalid data, missing pragma diagnostic states");
6637  FileID FID = ReadFileID(F, Record, Idx);
6638  assert(FID.isValid() && "invalid FileID for transition");
6639  unsigned Transitions = Record[Idx++];
6640 
6641  // Note that we don't need to set up Parent/ParentOffset here, because
6642  // we won't be changing the diagnostic state within imported FileIDs
6643  // (other than perhaps appending to the main source file, which has no
6644  // parent).
6645  auto &F = Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.Files[FID];
6646  F.StateTransitions.reserve(F.StateTransitions.size() + Transitions);
6647  for (unsigned I = 0; I != Transitions; ++I) {
6648  unsigned Offset = Record[Idx++];
6649  auto *State = ReadDiagState(*FirstState, false);
6650  F.StateTransitions.push_back({State, Offset});
6651  }
6652  }
6653 
6654  // Read the final state.
6655  assert(Idx < Record.size() &&
6656  "Invalid data, missing final pragma diagnostic state");
6657  SourceLocation CurStateLoc = ReadSourceLocation(F, Record[Idx++]);
6658  auto *CurState = ReadDiagState(*FirstState, false);
6659 
6660  if (!F.isModule()) {
6661  Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.CurDiagState = CurState;
6662  Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.CurDiagStateLoc = CurStateLoc;
6663 
6664  // Preserve the property that the imaginary root file describes the
6665  // current state.
6666  FileID NullFile;
6667  auto &T = Diag.DiagStatesByLoc.Files[NullFile].StateTransitions;
6668  if (T.empty())
6669  T.push_back({CurState, 0});
6670  else
6671  T[0].State = CurState;
6672  }
6673 
6674  // Don't try to read these mappings again.
6675  Record.clear();
6676  }
6677 }
6678 
6679 /// Get the correct cursor and offset for loading a type.
6680 ASTReader::RecordLocation ASTReader::TypeCursorForIndex(unsigned Index) {
6681  GlobalTypeMapType::iterator I = GlobalTypeMap.find(Index);
6682  assert(I != GlobalTypeMap.end() && "Corrupted global type map");
6683  ModuleFile *M = I->second;
6684  return RecordLocation(
6685  M, M->TypeOffsets[Index - M->BaseTypeIndex].getBitOffset() +
6686  M->DeclsBlockStartOffset);
6687 }
6688 
6689 static std::optional<Type::TypeClass> getTypeClassForCode(TypeCode code) {
6690  switch (code) {
6691 #define TYPE_BIT_CODE(CLASS_ID, CODE_ID, CODE_VALUE) \
6692  case TYPE_##CODE_ID: return Type::CLASS_ID;
6693 #include "clang/Serialization/TypeBitCodes.def"
6694  default:
6695  return std::nullopt;
6696  }
6697 }
6698 
6699 /// Read and return the type with the given index..
6700 ///
6701 /// The index is the type ID, shifted and minus the number of predefs. This
6702 /// routine actually reads the record corresponding to the type at the given
6703 /// location. It is a helper routine for GetType, which deals with reading type
6704 /// IDs.
6705 QualType ASTReader::readTypeRecord(unsigned Index) {
6706  assert(ContextObj && "reading type with no AST context");
6707  ASTContext &Context = *ContextObj;
6708  RecordLocation Loc = TypeCursorForIndex(Index);
6709  BitstreamCursor &DeclsCursor = Loc.F->DeclsCursor;
6710 
6711  // Keep track of where we are in the stream, then jump back there
6712  // after reading this type.
6713  SavedStreamPosition SavedPosition(DeclsCursor);
6714 
6715  ReadingKindTracker ReadingKind(Read_Type, *this);
6716 
6717  // Note that we are loading a type record.
6718  Deserializing AType(this);
6719 
6720  if (llvm::Error Err = DeclsCursor.JumpToBit(Loc.Offset)) {
6721  Error(std::move(Err));
6722  return QualType();
6723  }
6724  Expected<unsigned> RawCode = DeclsCursor.ReadCode();
6725  if (!RawCode) {
6726  Error(RawCode.takeError());
6727  return QualType();
6728  }
6729 
6730  ASTRecordReader Record(*this, *Loc.F);
6731  Expected<unsigned> Code = Record.readRecord(DeclsCursor, RawCode.get());
6732  if (!Code) {
6733  Error(Code.takeError());
6734  return QualType();
6735  }
6736  if (Code.get() == TYPE_EXT_QUAL) {
6737  QualType baseType = Record.readQualType();
6738  Qualifiers quals = Record.readQualifiers();
6739  return Context.getQualifiedType(baseType, quals);
6740  }
6741 
6742  auto maybeClass = getTypeClassForCode((TypeCode) Code.get());
6743  if (!maybeClass) {
6744  Error("Unexpected code for type");
6745  return QualType();
6746  }
6747 
6748  serialization::AbstractTypeReader<ASTRecordReader> TypeReader(Record);
6749  return TypeReader.read(*maybeClass);
6750 }

6754 class TypeLocReader : public TypeLocVisitor<TypeLocReader> {
6755  using LocSeq = SourceLocationSequence;
6756 
6757  ASTRecordReader &Reader;
6758  LocSeq *Seq;
6759 
6760  SourceLocation readSourceLocation() { return Reader.readSourceLocation(Seq); }
6761  SourceRange readSourceRange() { return Reader.readSourceRange(Seq); }
6762 
6763  TypeSourceInfo *GetTypeSourceInfo() {
6764  return Reader.readTypeSourceInfo();
6765  }
6766 
6767  NestedNameSpecifierLoc ReadNestedNameSpecifierLoc() {
6768  return Reader.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
6769  }
6770 
6771  Attr *ReadAttr() {
6772  return Reader.readAttr();
6773  }
6774 
6775 public:
6776  TypeLocReader(ASTRecordReader &Reader, LocSeq *Seq)
6777  : Reader(Reader), Seq(Seq) {}
6778 
6779  // We want compile-time assurance that we've enumerated all of
6780  // these, so unfortunately we have to declare them first, then
6781  // define them out-of-line.
6782 #define ABSTRACT_TYPELOC(CLASS, PARENT)
6783 #define TYPELOC(CLASS, PARENT) \
6784  void Visit##CLASS##TypeLoc(CLASS##TypeLoc TyLoc);
6785 #include "clang/AST/TypeLocNodes.def"
6786 
6787  void VisitFunctionTypeLoc(FunctionTypeLoc);
6788  void VisitArrayTypeLoc(ArrayTypeLoc);
6789 };

6975 ConceptReference *ASTRecordReader::readConceptReference() {
6976  auto NNS = readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
6977  auto TemplateKWLoc = readSourceLocation();
6978  auto ConceptNameLoc = readDeclarationNameInfo();
6979  auto FoundDecl = readDeclAs<NamedDecl>();
6980  auto NamedConcept = readDeclAs<ConceptDecl>();
6981  auto *CR = ConceptReference::Create(
6982  getContext(), NNS, TemplateKWLoc, ConceptNameLoc, FoundDecl, NamedConcept,
6983  (readBool() ? readASTTemplateArgumentListInfo() : nullptr));
6984  return CR;
6985 }

7132 void ASTRecordReader::readTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL, LocSeq *ParentSeq) {
7133  LocSeq::State Seq(ParentSeq);
7134  TypeLocReader TLR(*this, Seq);
7135  for (; !TL.isNull(); TL = TL.getNextTypeLoc())
7136  TLR.Visit(TL);
7137 }
7138 
7139 TypeSourceInfo *ASTRecordReader::readTypeSourceInfo() {
7140  QualType InfoTy = readType();
7141  if (InfoTy.isNull())
7142  return nullptr;
7143 
7144  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getContext().CreateTypeSourceInfo(InfoTy);
7145  readTypeLoc(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
7146  return TInfo;
7147 }
7148 
7149 QualType ASTReader::GetType(TypeID ID) {
7150  assert(ContextObj && "reading type with no AST context");
7151  ASTContext &Context = *ContextObj;
7152 
7153  unsigned FastQuals = ID & Qualifiers::FastMask;
7154  unsigned Index = ID >> Qualifiers::FastWidth;
7155 
7156  if (Index < NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS) {
7157  QualType T;
7158  switch ((PredefinedTypeIDs)Index) {
7159  case PREDEF_TYPE_LAST_ID:
7160  // We should never use this one.
7161  llvm_unreachable("Invalid predefined type");
7162  break;
7163  case PREDEF_TYPE_NULL_ID:
7164  return QualType();
7165  case PREDEF_TYPE_VOID_ID:
7166  T = Context.VoidTy;
7167  break;
7168  case PREDEF_TYPE_BOOL_ID:
7169  T = Context.BoolTy;
7170  break;
7171  case PREDEF_TYPE_CHAR_U_ID:
7172  case PREDEF_TYPE_CHAR_S_ID:
7173  // FIXME: Check that the signedness of CharTy is correct!
7174  T = Context.CharTy;
7175  break;
7176  case PREDEF_TYPE_UCHAR_ID:
7177  T = Context.UnsignedCharTy;
7178  break;
7179  case PREDEF_TYPE_USHORT_ID:
7180  T = Context.UnsignedShortTy;
7181  break;
7182  case PREDEF_TYPE_UINT_ID:
7183  T = Context.UnsignedIntTy;
7184  break;
7185  case PREDEF_TYPE_ULONG_ID:
7186  T = Context.UnsignedLongTy;
7187  break;
7188  case PREDEF_TYPE_ULONGLONG_ID:
7189  T = Context.UnsignedLongLongTy;
7190  break;
7191  case PREDEF_TYPE_UINT128_ID:
7192  T = Context.UnsignedInt128Ty;
7193  break;
7194  case PREDEF_TYPE_SCHAR_ID:
7195  T = Context.SignedCharTy;
7196  break;
7197  case PREDEF_TYPE_WCHAR_ID:
7198  T = Context.WCharTy;
7199  break;
7200  case PREDEF_TYPE_SHORT_ID:
7201  T = Context.ShortTy;
7202  break;
7203  case PREDEF_TYPE_INT_ID:
7204  T = Context.IntTy;
7205  break;
7206  case PREDEF_TYPE_LONG_ID:
7207  T = Context.LongTy;
7208  break;
7209  case PREDEF_TYPE_LONGLONG_ID:
7210  T = Context.LongLongTy;
7211  break;
7212  case PREDEF_TYPE_INT128_ID:
7213  T = Context.Int128Ty;
7214  break;
7215  case PREDEF_TYPE_BFLOAT16_ID:
7216  T = Context.BFloat16Ty;
7217  break;
7218  case PREDEF_TYPE_HALF_ID:
7219  T = Context.HalfTy;
7220  break;
7221  case PREDEF_TYPE_FLOAT_ID:
7222  T = Context.FloatTy;
7223  break;
7224  case PREDEF_TYPE_DOUBLE_ID:
7225  T = Context.DoubleTy;
7226  break;
7227  case PREDEF_TYPE_LONGDOUBLE_ID:
7228  T = Context.LongDoubleTy;
7229  break;

7448 
7449 serialization::TypeID
7450 ASTReader::getGlobalTypeID(ModuleFile &F, unsigned LocalID) const {
7451  unsigned FastQuals = LocalID & Qualifiers::FastMask;
7452  unsigned LocalIndex = LocalID >> Qualifiers::FastWidth;
7453 
7454  if (LocalIndex < NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS)
7455  return LocalID;
7456 
7457  if (!F.ModuleOffsetMap.empty())
7458  ReadModuleOffsetMap(F);
7459 
7460  ContinuousRangeMap<uint32_t, int, 2>::iterator I
7461  = F.TypeRemap.find(LocalIndex - NUM_PREDEF_TYPE_IDS);
7462  assert(I != F.TypeRemap.end() && "Invalid index into type index remap");
7463 
7464  unsigned GlobalIndex = LocalIndex + I->second;
7465  return (GlobalIndex << Qualifiers::FastWidth) | FastQuals;
7466 }
7467 
7468 TemplateArgumentLocInfo
7469 ASTRecordReader::readTemplateArgumentLocInfo(TemplateArgument::ArgKind Kind) {
7470  switch (Kind) {
7471  case TemplateArgument::Expression:
7472  return readExpr();
7473  case TemplateArgument::Type:
7474  return readTypeSourceInfo();
7475  case TemplateArgument::Template: {
7476  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc =
7477  readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
7478  SourceLocation TemplateNameLoc = readSourceLocation();
7479  return TemplateArgumentLocInfo(getASTContext(), QualifierLoc,
7480  TemplateNameLoc, SourceLocation());
7481  }
7482  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion: {
7483  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
7484  SourceLocation TemplateNameLoc = readSourceLocation();
7485  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = readSourceLocation();
7486  return TemplateArgumentLocInfo(getASTContext(), QualifierLoc,
7487  TemplateNameLoc, EllipsisLoc);
7488  }
7489  case TemplateArgument::Null:
7490  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
7491  case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
7492  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
7493  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue:
7494  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
7495  // FIXME: Is this right?
7496  return TemplateArgumentLocInfo();
7497  }
7498  llvm_unreachable("unexpected template argument loc");
7499 }
7500 
7501 TemplateArgumentLoc ASTRecordReader::readTemplateArgumentLoc() {
7502  TemplateArgument Arg = readTemplateArgument();
7503 
7504  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Expression) {
7505  if (readBool()) // bool InfoHasSameExpr.
7506  return TemplateArgumentLoc(Arg, TemplateArgumentLocInfo(Arg.getAsExpr()));
7507  }
7508  return TemplateArgumentLoc(Arg, readTemplateArgumentLocInfo(Arg.getKind()));
7509 }
7510 
7511 void ASTRecordReader::readTemplateArgumentListInfo(
7512  TemplateArgumentListInfo &Result) {
7513  Result.setLAngleLoc(readSourceLocation());
7514  Result.setRAngleLoc(readSourceLocation());
7515  unsigned NumArgsAsWritten = readInt();
7516  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgsAsWritten; ++i)
7517  Result.addArgument(readTemplateArgumentLoc());
7518 }
7519 
7520 const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *
7521 ASTRecordReader::readASTTemplateArgumentListInfo() {
7522  TemplateArgumentListInfo Result;
7523  readTemplateArgumentListInfo(Result);
7524  return ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo::Create(getContext(), Result);
7525 }

7530 
7531 void ASTReader::CompleteRedeclChain(const Decl *D) {
7532  if (NumCurrentElementsDeserializing) {
7533  // We arrange to not care about the complete redeclaration chain while we're
7534  // deserializing. Just remember that the AST has marked this one as complete
7535  // but that it's not actually complete yet, so we know we still need to
7536  // complete it later.
7537  PendingIncompleteDeclChains.push_back(const_cast<Decl*>(D));
7538  return;
7539  }
7540 
7541  if (!D->getDeclContext()) {
7542  assert(isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(D) && "Not a TU?");
7543  return;
7544  }
7545 
7546  const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
7547 
7548  // If this is a named declaration, complete it by looking it up
7549  // within its context.
7550  //
7551  // FIXME: Merging a function definition should merge
7552  // all mergeable entities within it.
7553  if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl, NamespaceDecl, RecordDecl, EnumDecl>(DC)) {
7554  if (DeclarationName Name = cast<NamedDecl>(D)->getDeclName()) {
7555  if (!getContext().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
7556  isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC)) {
7557  // Outside of C++, we don't have a lookup table for the TU, so update
7558  // the identifier instead. (For C++ modules, we don't store decls
7559  // in the serialized identifier table, so we do the lookup in the TU.)
7560  auto *II = Name.getAsIdentifierInfo();
7561  assert(II && "non-identifier name in C?");
7562  if (II->isOutOfDate())
7563  updateOutOfDateIdentifier(*II);
7564  } else
7565  DC->lookup(Name);
7566  } else if (needsAnonymousDeclarationNumber(cast<NamedDecl>(D))) {
7567  // Find all declarations of this kind from the relevant context.
7568  for (auto *DCDecl : cast<Decl>(D->getLexicalDeclContext())->redecls()) {
7569  auto *DC = cast<DeclContext>(DCDecl);
7570  SmallVector<Decl*, 8> Decls;
7571  FindExternalLexicalDecls(
7572  DC, [&](Decl::Kind K) { return K == D->getKind(); }, Decls);
7573  }
7574  }
7575  }
7576 
7577  if (auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D))
7578  CTSD->getSpecializedTemplate()->LoadLazySpecializations();
7579  if (auto *VTSD = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D))
7580  VTSD->getSpecializedTemplate()->LoadLazySpecializations();
7581  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
7582  if (auto *Template = FD->getPrimaryTemplate())
7583  Template->LoadLazySpecializations();
7584  }
7585 }
7586 
7587 CXXCtorInitializer **
7588 ASTReader::GetExternalCXXCtorInitializers(uint64_t Offset) {
7589  RecordLocation Loc = getLocalBitOffset(Offset);
7590  BitstreamCursor &Cursor = Loc.F->DeclsCursor;
7591  SavedStreamPosition SavedPosition(Cursor);
7592  if (llvm::Error Err = Cursor.JumpToBit(Loc.Offset)) {
7593  Error(std::move(Err));
7594  return nullptr;
7595  }
7596  ReadingKindTracker ReadingKind(Read_Decl, *this);
7597  Deserializing D(this);
7598 
7599  Expected<unsigned> MaybeCode = Cursor.ReadCode();
7600  if (!MaybeCode) {
7601  Error(MaybeCode.takeError());
7602  return nullptr;
7603  }
7604  unsigned Code = MaybeCode.get();
7605 
7606  ASTRecordReader Record(*this, *Loc.F);
7607  Expected<unsigned> MaybeRecCode = Record.readRecord(Cursor, Code);
7608  if (!MaybeRecCode) {
7609  Error(MaybeRecCode.takeError());
7610  return nullptr;
7611  }
7612  if (MaybeRecCode.get() != DECL_CXX_CTOR_INITIALIZERS) {
7613  Error("malformed AST file: missing C++ ctor initializers");
7614  return nullptr;
7615  }
7616 
7617  return Record.readCXXCtorInitializers();
7618 }
7619 
7620 CXXBaseSpecifier *ASTReader::GetExternalCXXBaseSpecifiers(uint64_t Offset) {
7621  assert(ContextObj && "reading base specifiers with no AST context");
7622  ASTContext &Context = *ContextObj;
7623 
7624  RecordLocation Loc = getLocalBitOffset(Offset);
7625  BitstreamCursor &Cursor = Loc.F->DeclsCursor;
7626  SavedStreamPosition SavedPosition(Cursor);
7627  if (llvm::Error Err = Cursor.JumpToBit(Loc.Offset)) {
7628  Error(std::move(Err));
7629  return nullptr;
7630  }
7631  ReadingKindTracker ReadingKind(Read_Decl, *this);
7632  Deserializing D(this);
7633 
7634  Expected<unsigned> MaybeCode = Cursor.ReadCode();
7635  if (!MaybeCode) {
7636  Error(MaybeCode.takeError());
7637  return nullptr;
7638  }
7639  unsigned Code = MaybeCode.get();
7640 
7641  ASTRecordReader Record(*this, *Loc.F);
7642  Expected<unsigned> MaybeRecCode = Record.readRecord(Cursor, Code);
7643  if (!MaybeRecCode) {
7644  Error(MaybeCode.takeError());
7645  return nullptr;
7646  }
7647  unsigned RecCode = MaybeRecCode.get();
7648 
7649  if (RecCode != DECL_CXX_BASE_SPECIFIERS) {
7650  Error("malformed AST file: missing C++ base specifiers");
7651  return nullptr;
7652  }
7653 
7654  unsigned NumBases = Record.readInt();
7655  void *Mem = Context.Allocate(sizeof(CXXBaseSpecifier) * NumBases);
7656  CXXBaseSpecifier *Bases = new (Mem) CXXBaseSpecifier [NumBases];
7657  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumBases; ++I)
7658  Bases[I] = Record.readCXXBaseSpecifier();
7659  return Bases;
7660 }
7661 
7662 GlobalDeclID ASTReader::getGlobalDeclID(ModuleFile &F,
7663  LocalDeclID LocalID) const {
7664  DeclID ID = LocalID.get();
7665  if (ID < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS)
7666  return GlobalDeclID(ID);
7667 
7668  if (!F.ModuleOffsetMap.empty())
7669  ReadModuleOffsetMap(F);
7670 
7671  ContinuousRangeMap<DeclID, int, 2>::iterator I =
7672  F.DeclRemap.find(ID - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS);
7673  assert(I != F.DeclRemap.end() && "Invalid index into decl index remap");
7674 
7675  return GlobalDeclID(ID + I->second);
7676 }
7677 
7678 bool ASTReader::isDeclIDFromModule(serialization::GlobalDeclID ID,
7679  ModuleFile &M) const {
7680  // Predefined decls aren't from any module.
7681  if (ID.get() < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS)
7682  return false;
7683 
7684  return ID.get() - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS >= M.BaseDeclID &&
7685  ID.get() - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS < M.BaseDeclID + M.LocalNumDecls;
7686 }
7687 
7688 ModuleFile *ASTReader::getOwningModuleFile(const Decl *D) {
7689  if (!D->isFromASTFile())
7690  return nullptr;
7691  GlobalDeclMapType::const_iterator I =
7692  GlobalDeclMap.find(GlobalDeclID(D->getGlobalID()));
7693  assert(I != GlobalDeclMap.end() && "Corrupted global declaration map");
7694  return I->second;
7695 }
7696 
7697 SourceLocation ASTReader::getSourceLocationForDeclID(GlobalDeclID ID) {
7698  if (ID.get() < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS)
7699  return SourceLocation();
7700 
7701  unsigned Index = ID.get() - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS;
7702 
7703  if (Index > DeclsLoaded.size()) {
7704  Error("declaration ID out-of-range for AST file");
7705  return SourceLocation();
7706  }
7707 
7708  if (Decl *D = DeclsLoaded[Index])
7709  return D->getLocation();
7710 
7711  SourceLocation Loc;
7712  DeclCursorForID(ID, Loc);
7713  return Loc;
7714 }

7716 static Decl *getPredefinedDecl(ASTContext &Context, PredefinedDeclIDs ID) {
7717  switch (ID) {
7718  case PREDEF_DECL_NULL_ID:
7719  return nullptr;
7720 
7721  case PREDEF_DECL_TRANSLATION_UNIT_ID:
7722  return Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
7723 
7724  case PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_ID_ID:
7725  return Context.getObjCIdDecl();
7726 
7727  case PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_SEL_ID:
7728  return Context.getObjCSelDecl();
7729 
7730  case PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_CLASS_ID:
7731  return Context.getObjCClassDecl();
7732 
7733  case PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_PROTOCOL_ID:
7734  return Context.getObjCProtocolDecl();
7735 
7736  case PREDEF_DECL_INT_128_ID:
7737  return Context.getInt128Decl();
7738 
7739  case PREDEF_DECL_UNSIGNED_INT_128_ID:
7740  return Context.getUInt128Decl();
7741 
7742  case PREDEF_DECL_OBJC_INSTANCETYPE_ID:
7743  return Context.getObjCInstanceTypeDecl();
7744 
7745  case PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_VA_LIST_ID:
7746  return Context.getBuiltinVaListDecl();
7747 
7748  case PREDEF_DECL_VA_LIST_TAG:
7749  return Context.getVaListTagDecl();
7750 
7751  case PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_VA_LIST_ID:
7752  return Context.getBuiltinMSVaListDecl();
7753 
7754  case PREDEF_DECL_BUILTIN_MS_GUID_ID:
7755  return Context.getMSGuidTagDecl();
7756 
7757  case PREDEF_DECL_EXTERN_C_CONTEXT_ID:
7758  return Context.getExternCContextDecl();
7759 
7760  case PREDEF_DECL_MAKE_INTEGER_SEQ_ID:
7761  return Context.getMakeIntegerSeqDecl();
7762 
7763  case PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_ID:
7764  return Context.getCFConstantStringDecl();
7765 
7766  case PREDEF_DECL_CF_CONSTANT_STRING_TAG_ID:
7767  return Context.getCFConstantStringTagDecl();
7768 
7769  case PREDEF_DECL_TYPE_PACK_ELEMENT_ID:
7770  return Context.getTypePackElementDecl();
7771  }
7772  llvm_unreachable("PredefinedDeclIDs unknown enum value");
7773 }
7774 
7775 Decl *ASTReader::GetExistingDecl(GlobalDeclID ID) {
7776  assert(ContextObj && "reading decl with no AST context");
7777  if (ID.get() < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS) {
7778  Decl *D = getPredefinedDecl(*ContextObj, (PredefinedDeclIDs)ID.get());
7779  if (D) {
7780  // Track that we have merged the declaration with ID \p ID into the
7781  // pre-existing predefined declaration \p D.
7782  auto &Merged = KeyDecls[D->getCanonicalDecl()];
7783  if (Merged.empty())
7784  Merged.push_back(ID);
7785  }
7786  return D;
7787  }
7788 
7789  unsigned Index = ID.get() - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS;
7790 
7791  if (Index >= DeclsLoaded.size()) {
7792  assert(0 && "declaration ID out-of-range for AST file");
7793  Error("declaration ID out-of-range for AST file");
7794  return nullptr;
7795  }
7796 
7797  return DeclsLoaded[Index];
7798 }
7799 
7800 Decl *ASTReader::GetDecl(GlobalDeclID ID) {
7801  if (ID.get() < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS)
7802  return GetExistingDecl(ID);
7803 
7804  unsigned Index = ID.get() - NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS;
7805 
7806  if (Index >= DeclsLoaded.size()) {
7807  assert(0 && "declaration ID out-of-range for AST file");
7808  Error("declaration ID out-of-range for AST file");
7809  return nullptr;
7810  }
7811 
7812  if (!DeclsLoaded[Index]) {
7813  ReadDeclRecord(ID);
7814  if (DeserializationListener)
7815  DeserializationListener->DeclRead(ID.get(), DeclsLoaded[Index]);
7816  }
7817 
7818  return DeclsLoaded[Index];
7819 }
7820 
7821 DeclID ASTReader::mapGlobalIDToModuleFileGlobalID(ModuleFile &M,
7822  GlobalDeclID GlobalID) {
7823  DeclID ID = GlobalID.get();
7824  if (ID < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS)
7825  return ID;
7826 
7827  GlobalDeclMapType::const_iterator I = GlobalDeclMap.find(GlobalID);
7828  assert(I != GlobalDeclMap.end() && "Corrupted global declaration map");
7829  ModuleFile *Owner = I->second;
7830 
7831  llvm::DenseMap<ModuleFile *, serialization::DeclID>::iterator Pos
7832  = M.GlobalToLocalDeclIDs.find(Owner);
7833  if (Pos == M.GlobalToLocalDeclIDs.end())
7834  return 0;
7835 
7836  return ID - Owner->BaseDeclID + Pos->second;
7837 }
7838 
7839 GlobalDeclID ASTReader::ReadDeclID(ModuleFile &F, const RecordData &Record,
7840  unsigned &Idx) {
7841  if (Idx >= Record.size()) {
7842  Error("Corrupted AST file");
7843  return GlobalDeclID(0);
7844  }
7845 
7846  return getGlobalDeclID(F, LocalDeclID(Record[Idx++]));
7847 }
7848 
7849 /// Resolve the offset of a statement into a statement.
7850 ///
7851 /// This operation will read a new statement from the external
7852 /// source each time it is called, and is meant to be used via a
7853 /// LazyOffsetPtr (which is used by Decls for the body of functions, etc).
7854 Stmt *ASTReader::GetExternalDeclStmt(uint64_t Offset) {
7855  // Switch case IDs are per Decl.
7856  ClearSwitchCaseIDs();
7857 
7858  // Offset here is a global offset across the entire chain.
7859  RecordLocation Loc = getLocalBitOffset(Offset);
7860  if (llvm::Error Err = Loc.F->DeclsCursor.JumpToBit(Loc.Offset)) {
7861  Error(std::move(Err));
7862  return nullptr;
7863  }
7864  assert(NumCurrentElementsDeserializing == 0 &&
7865  "should not be called while already deserializing");
7866  Deserializing D(this);
7867  return ReadStmtFromStream(*Loc.F);
7868 }
7869 
7870 void ASTReader::FindExternalLexicalDecls(
7871  const DeclContext *DC, llvm::function_ref<bool(Decl::Kind)> IsKindWeWant,
7872  SmallVectorImpl<Decl *> &Decls) {
7873  bool PredefsVisited[NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS] = {};
7874 
7875  auto Visit = [&] (ModuleFile *M, LexicalContents LexicalDecls) {
7876  assert(LexicalDecls.size() % 2 == 0 && "expected an even number of entries");
7877  for (int I = 0, N = LexicalDecls.size(); I != N; I += 2) {
7878  auto K = (Decl::Kind)+LexicalDecls[I];
7879  if (!IsKindWeWant(K))
7880  continue;
7881 
7882  auto ID = (serialization::DeclID)+LexicalDecls[I + 1];
7883 
7884  // Don't add predefined declarations to the lexical context more
7885  // than once.
7886  if (ID < NUM_PREDEF_DECL_IDS) {
7887  if (PredefsVisited[ID])
7888  continue;
7889 
7890  PredefsVisited[ID] = true;
7891  }
7892 
7893  if (Decl *D = GetLocalDecl(*M, LocalDeclID(ID))) {
7894  assert(D->getKind() == K && "wrong kind for lexical decl");
7895  if (!DC->isDeclInLexicalTraversal(D))
7896  Decls.push_back(D);
7897  }
7898  }
7899  };
7900 
7901  if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(DC)) {
7902  for (const auto &Lexical : TULexicalDecls)
7903  Visit(Lexical.first, Lexical.second);
7904  } else {
7905  auto I = LexicalDecls.find(DC);
7906  if (I != LexicalDecls.end())
7907  Visit(I->second.first, I->second.second);
7908  }
7909 
7910  ++NumLexicalDeclContextsRead;
7911 }

7913 namespace {
7914 
7915 class DeclIDComp {
7916  ASTReader &Reader;
7917  ModuleFile &Mod;
7918 
7919 public:
7920  DeclIDComp(ASTReader &Reader, ModuleFile &M) : Reader(Reader), Mod(M) {}
7921 
7922  bool operator()(LocalDeclID L, LocalDeclID R) const {
7923  SourceLocation LHS = getLocation(L);
7924  SourceLocation RHS = getLocation(R);
7925  return Reader.getSourceManager().isBeforeInTranslationUnit(LHS, RHS);
7926  }
7927 
7928  bool operator()(SourceLocation LHS, LocalDeclID R) const {
7929  SourceLocation RHS = getLocation(R);
7930  return Reader.getSourceManager().isBeforeInTranslationUnit(LHS, RHS);
7931  }
7932 
7933  bool operator()(LocalDeclID L, SourceLocation RHS) const {
7934  SourceLocation LHS = getLocation(L);
7935  return Reader.getSourceManager().isBeforeInTranslationUnit(LHS, RHS);
7936  }
7937 
7938  SourceLocation getLocation(LocalDeclID ID) const {
7939  return Reader.getSourceManager().getFileLoc(
7940  Reader.getSourceLocationForDeclID(Reader.getGlobalDeclID(Mod, ID)));
7941  }
7942 };
7943 
7944 } // namespace
7945 
7946 void ASTReader::FindFileRegionDecls(FileID File,
7947  unsigned Offset, unsigned Length,
7948  SmallVectorImpl<Decl *> &Decls) {
7949  SourceManager &SM = getSourceManager();
7950 
7951  llvm::DenseMap<FileID, FileDeclsInfo>::iterator I = FileDeclIDs.find(File);
7952  if (I == FileDeclIDs.end())
7953  return;
7954 
7955  FileDeclsInfo &DInfo = I->second;
7956  if (DInfo.Decls.empty())
7957  return;
7958 
7959  SourceLocation
7960  BeginLoc = SM.getLocForStartOfFile(File).getLocWithOffset(Offset);
7961  SourceLocation EndLoc = BeginLoc.getLocWithOffset(Length);
7962 
7963  DeclIDComp DIDComp(*this, *DInfo.Mod);
7964  ArrayRef<serialization::LocalDeclID>::iterator BeginIt =
7965  llvm::lower_bound(DInfo.Decls, BeginLoc, DIDComp);
7966  if (BeginIt != DInfo.Decls.begin())
7967  --BeginIt;
7968 
7969  // If we are pointing at a top-level decl inside an objc container, we need
7970  // to backtrack until we find it otherwise we will fail to report that the
7971  // region overlaps with an objc container.
7972  while (BeginIt != DInfo.Decls.begin() &&
7973  GetDecl(getGlobalDeclID(*DInfo.Mod, *BeginIt))
7974  ->isTopLevelDeclInObjCContainer())
7975  --BeginIt;
7976 
7977  ArrayRef<serialization::LocalDeclID>::iterator EndIt =
7978  llvm::upper_bound(DInfo.Decls, EndLoc, DIDComp);
7979  if (EndIt != DInfo.Decls.end())
7980  ++EndIt;
7981 
7982  for (ArrayRef<serialization::LocalDeclID>::iterator
7983  DIt = BeginIt; DIt != EndIt; ++DIt)
7984  Decls.push_back(GetDecl(getGlobalDeclID(*DInfo.Mod, *DIt)));
7985 }

7987 bool
7988 ASTReader::FindExternalVisibleDeclsByName(const DeclContext *DC,
7989  DeclarationName Name) {
7990  assert(DC->hasExternalVisibleStorage() && DC == DC->getPrimaryContext() &&
7991  "DeclContext has no visible decls in storage");
7992  if (!Name)
7993  return false;
7994 
7995  auto It = Lookups.find(DC);
7996  if (It == Lookups.end())
7997  return false;
7998 
7999  Deserializing LookupResults(this);
8000 
8001  // Load the list of declarations.
8002  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 64> Decls;
8003  llvm::SmallPtrSet<NamedDecl *, 8> Found;
8004  for (GlobalDeclID ID : It->second.Table.find(Name)) {
8005  NamedDecl *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(GetDecl(ID));
8006  if (ND->getDeclName() == Name && Found.insert(ND).second)
8007  Decls.push_back(ND);
8008  }
8009 
8010  ++NumVisibleDeclContextsRead;
8011  SetExternalVisibleDeclsForName(DC, Name, Decls);
8012  return !Decls.empty();
8013 }
8014 
8015 void ASTReader::completeVisibleDeclsMap(const DeclContext *DC) {
8016  if (!DC->hasExternalVisibleStorage())
8017  return;
8018 
8019  auto It = Lookups.find(DC);
8020  assert(It != Lookups.end() &&
8021  "have external visible storage but no lookup tables");
8022 
8023  DeclsMap Decls;
8024 
8025  for (GlobalDeclID ID : It->second.Table.findAll()) {
8026  NamedDecl *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(GetDecl(ID));
8027  Decls[ND->getDeclName()].push_back(ND);
8028  }
8029 
8030  ++NumVisibleDeclContextsRead;
8031 
8032  for (DeclsMap::iterator I = Decls.begin(), E = Decls.end(); I != E; ++I) {
8033  SetExternalVisibleDeclsForName(DC, I->first, I->second);
8034  }
8035  const_cast<DeclContext *>(DC)->setHasExternalVisibleStorage(false);
8036 }

8038 const serialization::reader::DeclContextLookupTable *
8039 ASTReader::getLoadedLookupTables(DeclContext *Primary) const {
8040  auto I = Lookups.find(Primary);
8041  return I == Lookups.end() ? nullptr : &I->second;
8042 }

8044 /// Under non-PCH compilation the consumer receives the objc methods
8045 /// before receiving the implementation, and codegen depends on this.
8046 /// We simulate this by deserializing and passing to consumer the methods of the
8047 /// implementation before passing the deserialized implementation decl.
8048 static void PassObjCImplDeclToConsumer(ObjCImplDecl *ImplD,
8049  ASTConsumer *Consumer) {
8050  assert(ImplD && Consumer);
8051 
8052  for (auto *I : ImplD->methods())
8053  Consumer->HandleInterestingDecl(DeclGroupRef(I));
8054 
8055  Consumer->HandleInterestingDecl(DeclGroupRef(ImplD));
8056 }
8057 
8058 void ASTReader::PassInterestingDeclToConsumer(Decl *D) {
8059  if (ObjCImplDecl *ImplD = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(D))
8060  PassObjCImplDeclToConsumer(ImplD, Consumer);
8061  else
8062  Consumer->HandleInterestingDecl(DeclGroupRef(D));
8063 }
8064 
8065 void ASTReader::StartTranslationUnit(ASTConsumer *Consumer) {
8066  this->Consumer = Consumer;
8067 
8068  if (Consumer)
8069  PassInterestingDeclsToConsumer();
8070 
8071  if (DeserializationListener)
8072  DeserializationListener->ReaderInitialized(this);
8073 }

8075 void ASTReader::PrintStats() {
8076  std::fprintf(stderr, "*** AST File Statistics:\n");
8077 
8078  unsigned NumTypesLoaded =
8079  TypesLoaded.size() - llvm::count(TypesLoaded.materialized(), QualType());
8080  unsigned NumDeclsLoaded =
8081  DeclsLoaded.size() -
8082  llvm::count(DeclsLoaded.materialized(), (Decl *)nullptr);
8083  unsigned NumIdentifiersLoaded =
8084  IdentifiersLoaded.size() -
8085  llvm::count(IdentifiersLoaded, (IdentifierInfo *)nullptr);
8086  unsigned NumMacrosLoaded =
8087  MacrosLoaded.size() - llvm::count(MacrosLoaded, (MacroInfo *)nullptr);
8088  unsigned NumSelectorsLoaded =
8089  SelectorsLoaded.size() - llvm::count(SelectorsLoaded, Selector());
8090 
8091  if (unsigned TotalNumSLocEntries = getTotalNumSLocs())
8092  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u source location entries read (%f%%)\n",
8093  NumSLocEntriesRead, TotalNumSLocEntries,
8094  ((float)NumSLocEntriesRead/TotalNumSLocEntries * 100));
8095  if (!TypesLoaded.empty())
8096  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u types read (%f%%)\n",
8097  NumTypesLoaded, (unsigned)TypesLoaded.size(),
8098  ((float)NumTypesLoaded/TypesLoaded.size() * 100));
8099  if (!DeclsLoaded.empty())
8100  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u declarations read (%f%%)\n",
8101  NumDeclsLoaded, (unsigned)DeclsLoaded.size(),
8102  ((float)NumDeclsLoaded/DeclsLoaded.size() * 100));
8103  if (!IdentifiersLoaded.empty())
8104  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u identifiers read (%f%%)\n",
8105  NumIdentifiersLoaded, (unsigned)IdentifiersLoaded.size(),
8106  ((float)NumIdentifiersLoaded/IdentifiersLoaded.size() * 100));
8107  if (!MacrosLoaded.empty())
8108  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u macros read (%f%%)\n",
8109  NumMacrosLoaded, (unsigned)MacrosLoaded.size(),
8110  ((float)NumMacrosLoaded/MacrosLoaded.size() * 100));
8111  if (!SelectorsLoaded.empty())
8112  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u selectors read (%f%%)\n",
8113  NumSelectorsLoaded, (unsigned)SelectorsLoaded.size(),
8114  ((float)NumSelectorsLoaded/SelectorsLoaded.size() * 100));
8115  if (TotalNumStatements)
8116  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u statements read (%f%%)\n",
8117  NumStatementsRead, TotalNumStatements,
8118  ((float)NumStatementsRead/TotalNumStatements * 100));
8119  if (TotalNumMacros)
8120  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u macros read (%f%%)\n",
8121  NumMacrosRead, TotalNumMacros,
8122  ((float)NumMacrosRead/TotalNumMacros * 100));
8123  if (TotalLexicalDeclContexts)
8124  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u lexical declcontexts read (%f%%)\n",
8125  NumLexicalDeclContextsRead, TotalLexicalDeclContexts,
8126  ((float)NumLexicalDeclContextsRead/TotalLexicalDeclContexts
8127  * 100));
8128  if (TotalVisibleDeclContexts)
8129  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u visible declcontexts read (%f%%)\n",
8130  NumVisibleDeclContextsRead, TotalVisibleDeclContexts,
8131  ((float)NumVisibleDeclContextsRead/TotalVisibleDeclContexts
8132  * 100));
8133  if (TotalNumMethodPoolEntries)
8134  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u method pool entries read (%f%%)\n",
8135  NumMethodPoolEntriesRead, TotalNumMethodPoolEntries,
8136  ((float)NumMethodPoolEntriesRead/TotalNumMethodPoolEntries
8137  * 100));
8138  if (NumMethodPoolLookups)
8139  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u method pool lookups succeeded (%f%%)\n",
8140  NumMethodPoolHits, NumMethodPoolLookups,
8141  ((float)NumMethodPoolHits/NumMethodPoolLookups * 100.0));
8142  if (NumMethodPoolTableLookups)
8143  std::fprintf(stderr, " %u/%u method pool table lookups succeeded (%f%%)\n",
8144  NumMethodPoolTableHits, NumMethodPoolTableLookups,
8145  ((float)NumMethodPoolTableHits/NumMethodPoolTableLookups
8146  * 100.0));
8147  if (NumIdentifierLookupHits)
8148  std::fprintf(stderr,
8149  " %u / %u identifier table lookups succeeded (%f%%)\n",
8150  NumIdentifierLookupHits, NumIdentifierLookups,
8151  (double)NumIdentifierLookupHits*100.0/NumIdentifierLookups);
8152 
8153  if (GlobalIndex) {
8154  std::fprintf(stderr, "\n");
8155  GlobalIndex->printStats();
8156  }
8157 
8158  std::fprintf(stderr, "\n");
8159  dump();
8160  std::fprintf(stderr, "\n");
8161 }

8163 template<typename Key, typename ModuleFile, unsigned InitialCapacity>
8164 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD static void
8165 dumpModuleIDMap(StringRef Name,
8166  const ContinuousRangeMap<Key, ModuleFile *,
8167  InitialCapacity> &Map) {
8168  if (Map.begin() == Map.end())
8169  return;
8170 
8171  using MapType = ContinuousRangeMap<Key, ModuleFile *, InitialCapacity>;
8172 
8173  llvm::errs() << Name << ":\n";
8174  for (typename MapType::const_iterator I = Map.begin(), IEnd = Map.end();
8175  I != IEnd; ++I) {
8176  uint64_t ID = 0;
8177  if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<Key>)
8178  ID = I->first;
8179  else /*GlobalDeclID*/
8180  ID = I->first.get();
8181  llvm::errs() << " " << ID << " -> " << I->second->FileName << "\n";
8182  }
8183 }

8185 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void ASTReader::dump() {
8186  llvm::errs() << "*** PCH/ModuleFile Remappings:\n";
8187  dumpModuleIDMap("Global bit offset map", GlobalBitOffsetsMap);
8188  dumpModuleIDMap("Global source location entry map", GlobalSLocEntryMap);
8189  dumpModuleIDMap("Global type map", GlobalTypeMap);
8190  dumpModuleIDMap("Global declaration map", GlobalDeclMap);
8191  dumpModuleIDMap("Global identifier map", GlobalIdentifierMap);
8192  dumpModuleIDMap("Global macro map", GlobalMacroMap);
8193  dumpModuleIDMap("Global submodule map", GlobalSubmoduleMap);
8194  dumpModuleIDMap("Global selector map", GlobalSelectorMap);
8195  dumpModuleIDMap("Global preprocessed entity map",
8196  GlobalPreprocessedEntityMap);
8197 
8198  llvm::errs() << "\n*** PCH/Modules Loaded:";
8199  for (ModuleFile &M : ModuleMgr)
8200  M.dump();
8201 }

8203 /// Return the amount of memory used by memory buffers, breaking down
8204 /// by heap-backed versus mmap'ed memory.
8205 void ASTReader::getMemoryBufferSizes(MemoryBufferSizes &sizes) const {
8206  for (ModuleFile &I : ModuleMgr) {
8207  if (llvm::MemoryBuffer *buf = I.Buffer) {
8208  size_t bytes = buf->getBufferSize();
8209  switch (buf->getBufferKind()) {
8210  case llvm::MemoryBuffer::MemoryBuffer_Malloc:
8211  sizes.malloc_bytes += bytes;
8212  break;
8213  case llvm::MemoryBuffer::MemoryBuffer_MMap:
8214  sizes.mmap_bytes += bytes;
8215  break;
8216  }
8217  }
8218  }
8219 }

8221 void ASTReader::InitializeSema(Sema &S) {
8222  SemaObj = &S;
8223  S.addExternalSource(this);
8224 
8225  // Makes sure any declarations that were deserialized "too early"
8226  // still get added to the identifier's declaration chains.
8227  for (GlobalDeclID ID : PreloadedDeclIDs) {
8228  NamedDecl *D = cast<NamedDecl>(GetDecl(ID));
8229  pushExternalDeclIntoScope(D, D->getDeclName());
8230  }
8231  PreloadedDeclIDs.clear();
8232 
8233  // FIXME: What happens if these are changed by a module import?
8234  if (!FPPragmaOptions.empty()) {
8235  assert(FPPragmaOptions.size() == 1 && "Wrong number of FP_PRAGMA_OPTIONS");
8236  FPOptionsOverride NewOverrides =
8237  FPOptionsOverride::getFromOpaqueInt(FPPragmaOptions[0]);
8238  SemaObj->CurFPFeatures =
8239  NewOverrides.applyOverrides(SemaObj->getLangOpts());
8240  }
8241 
8242  SemaObj->OpenCLFeatures = OpenCLExtensions;
8243 
8244  UpdateSema();
8245 }
8246 
8247 void ASTReader::UpdateSema() {
8248  assert(SemaObj && "no Sema to update");
8249 
8250  // Load the offsets of the declarations that Sema references.
8251  // They will be lazily deserialized when needed.
8252  if (!SemaDeclRefs.empty()) {
8253  assert(SemaDeclRefs.size() % 3 == 0);
8254  for (unsigned I = 0; I != SemaDeclRefs.size(); I += 3) {
8255  if (!SemaObj->StdNamespace)
8256  SemaObj->StdNamespace = SemaDeclRefs[I].get();
8257  if (!SemaObj->StdBadAlloc)
8258  SemaObj->StdBadAlloc = SemaDeclRefs[I + 1].get();
8259  if (!SemaObj->StdAlignValT)
8260  SemaObj->StdAlignValT = SemaDeclRefs[I + 2].get();
8261  }
8262  SemaDeclRefs.clear();
8263  }
8264 
8265  // Update the state of pragmas. Use the same API as if we had encountered the
8266  // pragma in the source.
8267  if(OptimizeOffPragmaLocation.isValid())
8268  SemaObj->ActOnPragmaOptimize(/* On = */ false, OptimizeOffPragmaLocation);
8269  if (PragmaMSStructState != -1)
8270  SemaObj->ActOnPragmaMSStruct((PragmaMSStructKind)PragmaMSStructState);
8271  if (PointersToMembersPragmaLocation.isValid()) {
8272  SemaObj->ActOnPragmaMSPointersToMembers(
8273  (LangOptions::PragmaMSPointersToMembersKind)
8274  PragmaMSPointersToMembersState,
8275  PointersToMembersPragmaLocation);
8276  }
8277  SemaObj->CUDA().ForceHostDeviceDepth = ForceHostDeviceDepth;
8278 
8279  if (PragmaAlignPackCurrentValue) {
8280  // The bottom of the stack might have a default value. It must be adjusted
8281  // to the current value to ensure that the packing state is preserved after
8282  // popping entries that were included/imported from a PCH/module.
8283  bool DropFirst = false;
8284  if (!PragmaAlignPackStack.empty() &&
8285  PragmaAlignPackStack.front().Location.isInvalid()) {
8286  assert(PragmaAlignPackStack.front().Value ==
8287  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.DefaultValue &&
8288  "Expected a default alignment value");
8289  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.Stack.emplace_back(
8290  PragmaAlignPackStack.front().SlotLabel,
8291  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.CurrentValue,
8292  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.CurrentPragmaLocation,
8293  PragmaAlignPackStack.front().PushLocation);
8294  DropFirst = true;
8295  }
8296  for (const auto &Entry :
8297  llvm::ArrayRef(PragmaAlignPackStack).drop_front(DropFirst ? 1 : 0)) {
8298  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.Stack.emplace_back(
8299  Entry.SlotLabel, Entry.Value, Entry.Location, Entry.PushLocation);
8300  }
8301  if (PragmaAlignPackCurrentLocation.isInvalid()) {
8302  assert(*PragmaAlignPackCurrentValue ==
8303  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.DefaultValue &&
8304  "Expected a default align and pack value");
8305  // Keep the current values.
8306  } else {
8307  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.CurrentValue = *PragmaAlignPackCurrentValue;
8308  SemaObj->AlignPackStack.CurrentPragmaLocation =
8309  PragmaAlignPackCurrentLocation;
8310  }
8311  }
8312  if (FpPragmaCurrentValue) {
8313  // The bottom of the stack might have a default value. It must be adjusted
8314  // to the current value to ensure that fp-pragma state is preserved after
8315  // popping entries that were included/imported from a PCH/module.
8316  bool DropFirst = false;
8317  if (!FpPragmaStack.empty() && FpPragmaStack.front().Location.isInvalid()) {
8318  assert(FpPragmaStack.front().Value ==
8319  SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.DefaultValue &&
8320  "Expected a default pragma float_control value");
8321  SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.Stack.emplace_back(
8322  FpPragmaStack.front().SlotLabel, SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue,
8323  SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.CurrentPragmaLocation,
8324  FpPragmaStack.front().PushLocation);
8325  DropFirst = true;
8326  }
8327  for (const auto &Entry :
8328  llvm::ArrayRef(FpPragmaStack).drop_front(DropFirst ? 1 : 0))
8329  SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.Stack.emplace_back(
8330  Entry.SlotLabel, Entry.Value, Entry.Location, Entry.PushLocation);
8331  if (FpPragmaCurrentLocation.isInvalid()) {
8332  assert(*FpPragmaCurrentValue == SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.DefaultValue &&
8333  "Expected a default pragma float_control value");
8334  // Keep the current values.
8335  } else {
8336  SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue = *FpPragmaCurrentValue;
8337  SemaObj->FpPragmaStack.CurrentPragmaLocation = FpPragmaCurrentLocation;
8338  }
8339  }
8340 
8341  // For non-modular AST files, restore visiblity of modules.
8342  for (auto &Import : PendingImportedModulesSema) {
8343  if (Import.ImportLoc.isInvalid())
8344  continue;
8345  if (Module *Imported = getSubmodule(Import.ID)) {
8346  SemaObj->makeModuleVisible(Imported, Import.ImportLoc);
8347  }
8348  }
8349  PendingImportedModulesSema.clear();
8350 }
8351 
8352 IdentifierInfo *ASTReader::get(StringRef Name) {
8353  // Note that we are loading an identifier.
8354  Deserializing AnIdentifier(this);
8355 
8356  IdentifierLookupVisitor Visitor(Name, /*PriorGeneration=*/0,
8357  NumIdentifierLookups,
8358  NumIdentifierLookupHits);
8359 
8360  // We don't need to do identifier table lookups in C++ modules (we preload
8361  // all interesting declarations, and don't need to use the scope for name
8362  // lookups). Perform the lookup in PCH files, though, since we don't build
8363  // a complete initial identifier table if we're carrying on from a PCH.
8364  if (PP.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
8365  for (auto *F : ModuleMgr.pch_modules())
8366  if (Visitor(*F))
8367  break;
8368  } else {
8369  // If there is a global index, look there first to determine which modules
8370  // provably do not have any results for this identifier.
8371  GlobalModuleIndex::HitSet Hits;
8372  GlobalModuleIndex::HitSet *HitsPtr = nullptr;
8373  if (!loadGlobalIndex()) {
8374  if (GlobalIndex->lookupIdentifier(Name, Hits)) {
8375  HitsPtr = &Hits;
8376  }
8377  }
8378 
8379  ModuleMgr.visit(Visitor, HitsPtr);
8380  }
8381 
8382  IdentifierInfo *II = Visitor.getIdentifierInfo();
8383  markIdentifierUpToDate(II);
8384  return II;
8385 }
8386 
8387 namespace clang {
8388 
8389  /// An identifier-lookup iterator that enumerates all of the
8390  /// identifiers stored within a set of AST files.
8391  class ASTIdentifierIterator : public IdentifierIterator {
8392  /// The AST reader whose identifiers are being enumerated.
8393  const ASTReader &Reader;
8394 
8395  /// The current index into the chain of AST files stored in
8396  /// the AST reader.
8397  unsigned Index;
8398 
8399  /// The current position within the identifier lookup table
8400  /// of the current AST file.
8401  ASTIdentifierLookupTable::key_iterator Current;
8402 
8403  /// The end position within the identifier lookup table of
8404  /// the current AST file.
8405  ASTIdentifierLookupTable::key_iterator End;
8406 
8407  /// Whether to skip any modules in the ASTReader.
8408  bool SkipModules;
8409 
8410  public:
8411  explicit ASTIdentifierIterator(const ASTReader &Reader,
8412  bool SkipModules = false);
8413 
8414  StringRef Next() override;
8415  };
8416 
8417 } // namespace clang
8418 
8419 ASTIdentifierIterator::ASTIdentifierIterator(const ASTReader &Reader,
8420  bool SkipModules)
8421  : Reader(Reader), Index(Reader.ModuleMgr.size()), SkipModules(SkipModules) {
8422 }
8423 
8424 StringRef ASTIdentifierIterator::Next() {
8425  while (Current == End) {
8426  // If we have exhausted all of our AST files, we're done.
8427  if (Index == 0)
8428  return StringRef();
8429 
8430  --Index;
8431  ModuleFile &F = Reader.ModuleMgr[Index];
8432  if (SkipModules && F.isModule())
8433  continue;
8434 
8435  ASTIdentifierLookupTable *IdTable =
8436  (ASTIdentifierLookupTable *)F.IdentifierLookupTable;
8437  Current = IdTable->key_begin();
8438  End = IdTable->key_end();
8439  }
8440 
8441  // We have any identifiers remaining in the current AST file; return
8442  // the next one.
8443  StringRef Result = *Current;
8444  ++Current;
8445  return Result;
8446 }
8447 
8448 namespace {
8449 
8450 /// A utility for appending two IdentifierIterators.
8451 class ChainedIdentifierIterator : public IdentifierIterator {
8452  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> Current;
8453  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> Queued;
8454 
8455 public:
8456  ChainedIdentifierIterator(std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> First,
8457  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> Second)
8458  : Current(std::move(First)), Queued(std::move(Second)) {}
8459 
8460  StringRef Next() override {
8461  if (!Current)
8462  return StringRef();
8463 
8464  StringRef result = Current->Next();
8465  if (!result.empty())
8466  return result;
8467 
8468  // Try the queued iterator, which may itself be empty.
8469  Current.reset();
8470  std::swap(Current, Queued);
8471  return Next();
8472  }
8473 };
8474 
8475 } // namespace
8476 
8477 IdentifierIterator *ASTReader::getIdentifiers() {
8478  if (!loadGlobalIndex()) {
8479  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> ReaderIter(
8480  new ASTIdentifierIterator(*this, /*SkipModules=*/true));
8481  std::unique_ptr<IdentifierIterator> ModulesIter(
8482  GlobalIndex->createIdentifierIterator());
8483  return new ChainedIdentifierIterator(std::move(ReaderIter),
8484  std::move(ModulesIter));
8485  }
8486 
8487  return new ASTIdentifierIterator(*this);
8488 }

8490 namespace clang {

8492 
8493  class ReadMethodPoolVisitor {
8494  ASTReader &Reader;
8495  Selector Sel;
8496  unsigned PriorGeneration;
8497  unsigned InstanceBits = 0;
8498  unsigned FactoryBits = 0;
8499  bool InstanceHasMoreThanOneDecl = false;
8500  bool FactoryHasMoreThanOneDecl = false;
8501  SmallVector<ObjCMethodDecl *, 4> InstanceMethods;
8502  SmallVector<ObjCMethodDecl *, 4> FactoryMethods;
8503 
8504  public:
8505  ReadMethodPoolVisitor(ASTReader &Reader, Selector Sel,
8506  unsigned PriorGeneration)
8507  : Reader(Reader), Sel(Sel), PriorGeneration(PriorGeneration) {}
8508 
8509  bool operator()(ModuleFile &M) {
8510  if (!M.SelectorLookupTable)
8511  return false;
8512 
8513  // If we've already searched this module file, skip it now.
8514  if (M.Generation <= PriorGeneration)
8515  return true;
8516 
8517  ++Reader.NumMethodPoolTableLookups;
8518  ASTSelectorLookupTable *PoolTable
8519  = (ASTSelectorLookupTable*)M.SelectorLookupTable;
8520  ASTSelectorLookupTable::iterator Pos = PoolTable->find(Sel);
8521  if (Pos == PoolTable->end())
8522  return false;
8523 
8524  ++Reader.NumMethodPoolTableHits;
8525  ++Reader.NumSelectorsRead;
8526  // FIXME: Not quite happy with the statistics here. We probably should
8527  // disable this tracking when called via LoadSelector.
8528  // Also, should entries without methods count as misses?
8529  ++Reader.NumMethodPoolEntriesRead;
8530  ASTSelectorLookupTrait::data_type Data = *Pos;
8531  if (Reader.DeserializationListener)
8532  Reader.DeserializationListener->SelectorRead(Data.ID, Sel);
8533 
8534  // Append methods in the reverse order, so that later we can process them
8535  // in the order they appear in the source code by iterating through
8536  // the vector in the reverse order.
8537  InstanceMethods.append(Data.Instance.rbegin(), Data.Instance.rend());
8538  FactoryMethods.append(Data.Factory.rbegin(), Data.Factory.rend());
8539  InstanceBits = Data.InstanceBits;
8540  FactoryBits = Data.FactoryBits;
8541  InstanceHasMoreThanOneDecl = Data.InstanceHasMoreThanOneDecl;
8542  FactoryHasMoreThanOneDecl = Data.FactoryHasMoreThanOneDecl;
8543  return false;
8544  }
8545 
8546  /// Retrieve the instance methods found by this visitor.
8547  ArrayRef<ObjCMethodDecl *> getInstanceMethods() const {
8548  return InstanceMethods;
8549  }
8550 
8551  /// Retrieve the instance methods found by this visitor.
8552  ArrayRef<ObjCMethodDecl *> getFactoryMethods() const {
8553  return FactoryMethods;
8554  }
8555 
8556  unsigned getInstanceBits() const { return InstanceBits; }
8557  unsigned getFactoryBits() const { return FactoryBits; }
8558 
8559  bool instanceHasMoreThanOneDecl() const {
8560  return InstanceHasMoreThanOneDecl;
8561  }
8562 
8563  bool factoryHasMoreThanOneDecl() const { return FactoryHasMoreThanOneDecl; }
8564  };
8565 
8566 } // namespace serialization
8567 } // namespace clang
8568 
8569 /// Add the given set of methods to the method list.
8570 static void addMethodsToPool(Sema &S, ArrayRef<ObjCMethodDecl *> Methods,
8571  ObjCMethodList &List) {
8572  for (ObjCMethodDecl *M : llvm::reverse(Methods))
8573  S.addMethodToGlobalList(&List, M);
8574 }
8575 
8576 void ASTReader::ReadMethodPool(Selector Sel) {
8577  // Get the selector generation and update it to the current generation.
8578  unsigned &Generation = SelectorGeneration[Sel];
8579  unsigned PriorGeneration = Generation;
8580  Generation = getGeneration();
8581  SelectorOutOfDate[Sel] = false;
8582 
8583  // Search for methods defined with this selector.
8584  ++NumMethodPoolLookups;
8585  ReadMethodPoolVisitor Visitor(*this, Sel, PriorGeneration);
8586  ModuleMgr.visit(Visitor);
8587 
8588  if (Visitor.getInstanceMethods().empty() &&
8589  Visitor.getFactoryMethods().empty())
8590  return;
8591 
8592  ++NumMethodPoolHits;
8593 
8594  if (!getSema())
8595  return;
8596 
8597  Sema &S = *getSema();
8598  Sema::GlobalMethodPool::iterator Pos =
8599  S.MethodPool.insert(std::make_pair(Sel, Sema::GlobalMethodPool::Lists()))
8600  .first;
8601 
8602  Pos->second.first.setBits(Visitor.getInstanceBits());
8603  Pos->second.first.setHasMoreThanOneDecl(Visitor.instanceHasMoreThanOneDecl());
8604  Pos->second.second.setBits(Visitor.getFactoryBits());
8605  Pos->second.second.setHasMoreThanOneDecl(Visitor.factoryHasMoreThanOneDecl());
8606 
8607  // Add methods to the global pool *after* setting hasMoreThanOneDecl, since
8608  // when building a module we keep every method individually and may need to
8609  // update hasMoreThanOneDecl as we add the methods.
8610  addMethodsToPool(S, Visitor.getInstanceMethods(), Pos->second.first);
8611  addMethodsToPool(S, Visitor.getFactoryMethods(), Pos->second.second);
8612 }
8613 
8614 void ASTReader::updateOutOfDateSelector(Selector Sel) {
8615  if (SelectorOutOfDate[Sel])
8616  ReadMethodPool(Sel);
8617 }

8641 void ASTReader::ReadMismatchingDeleteExpressions(llvm::MapVector<
8642  FieldDecl *, llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<SourceLocation, bool>, 4>> &
8643  Exprs) {

8721 void ASTReader::ReadReferencedSelectors(
8722  SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<Selector, SourceLocation>> &Sels) {
8723  if (ReferencedSelectorsData.empty())
8724  return;
8725 
8726  // If there are @selector references added them to its pool. This is for
8727  // implementation of -Wselector.
8728  unsigned int DataSize = ReferencedSelectorsData.size()-1;
8729  unsigned I = 0;
8730  while (I < DataSize) {
8731  Selector Sel = DecodeSelector(ReferencedSelectorsData[I++]);
8732  SourceLocation SelLoc
8733  = SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(ReferencedSelectorsData[I++]);
8734  Sels.push_back(std::make_pair(Sel, SelLoc));
8735  }
8736  ReferencedSelectorsData.clear();
8737 }

8739 void ASTReader::ReadWeakUndeclaredIdentifiers(
8740  SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<IdentifierInfo *, WeakInfo>> &WeakIDs) {
8741  if (WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.empty())
8742  return;
8743 
8744  for (unsigned I = 0, N = WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.size(); I < N; /*none*/) {
8745  IdentifierInfo *WeakId
8746  = DecodeIdentifierInfo(WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers[I++]);
8747  IdentifierInfo *AliasId
8748  = DecodeIdentifierInfo(WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers[I++]);
8749  SourceLocation Loc =
8750  SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers[I++]);
8751  WeakInfo WI(AliasId, Loc);
8752  WeakIDs.push_back(std::make_pair(WeakId, WI));
8753  }
8754  WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.clear();
8755 }

8782 void ASTReader::ReadLateParsedTemplates(
8783  llvm::MapVector<const FunctionDecl *, std::unique_ptr<LateParsedTemplate>>
8784  &LPTMap) {
8785  for (auto &LPT : LateParsedTemplates) {
8786  ModuleFile *FMod = LPT.first;
8787  RecordDataImpl &LateParsed = LPT.second;
8788  for (unsigned Idx = 0, N = LateParsed.size(); Idx < N;
8789  /* In loop */) {
8790  FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(
8791  GetLocalDecl(*FMod, LocalDeclID(LateParsed[Idx++])));
8792 
8793  auto LT = std::make_unique<LateParsedTemplate>();
8794  LT->D = GetLocalDecl(*FMod, LocalDeclID(LateParsed[Idx++]));
8795  LT->FPO = FPOptions::getFromOpaqueInt(LateParsed[Idx++]);
8796 
8797  ModuleFile *F = getOwningModuleFile(LT->D);
8798  assert(F && "No module");
8799 
8800  unsigned TokN = LateParsed[Idx++];
8801  LT->Toks.reserve(TokN);
8802  for (unsigned T = 0; T < TokN; ++T)
8803  LT->Toks.push_back(ReadToken(*F, LateParsed, Idx));
8804 
8805  LPTMap.insert(std::make_pair(FD, std::move(LT)));
8806  }
8807  }
8808 
8809  LateParsedTemplates.clear();
8810 }

8812 void ASTReader::AssignedLambdaNumbering(const CXXRecordDecl *Lambda) {
8813  if (Lambda->getLambdaContextDecl()) {
8814  // Keep track of this lambda so it can be merged with another lambda that
8815  // is loaded later.
8816  LambdaDeclarationsForMerging.insert(
8817  {{Lambda->getLambdaContextDecl()->getCanonicalDecl(),
8818  Lambda->getLambdaIndexInContext()},
8819  const_cast<CXXRecordDecl *>(Lambda)});
8820  }
8821 }

8825  ReadMethodPool(Sel);

8828 void ASTReader::SetIdentifierInfo(IdentifierID ID, IdentifierInfo *II) {
8829  assert(ID && "Non-zero identifier ID required");
8830  assert(ID <= IdentifiersLoaded.size() && "identifier ID out of range");
8831  IdentifiersLoaded[ID - 1] = II;
8832  if (DeserializationListener)
8833  DeserializationListener->IdentifierRead(ID, II);
8834 }
8835 
8836 /// Set the globally-visible declarations associated with the given
8837 /// identifier.
8838 ///
8839 /// If the AST reader is currently in a state where the given declaration IDs
8840 /// cannot safely be resolved, they are queued until it is safe to resolve
8841 /// them.
8842 ///
8843 /// \param II an IdentifierInfo that refers to one or more globally-visible
8844 /// declarations.
8845 ///
8846 /// \param DeclIDs the set of declaration IDs with the name @p II that are
8847 /// visible at global scope.
8848 ///
8849 /// \param Decls if non-null, this vector will be populated with the set of
8850 /// deserialized declarations. These declarations will not be pushed into
8851 /// scope.
8852 void ASTReader::SetGloballyVisibleDecls(
8853  IdentifierInfo *II, const SmallVectorImpl<GlobalDeclID> &DeclIDs,
8854  SmallVectorImpl<Decl *> *Decls) {
8855  if (NumCurrentElementsDeserializing && !Decls) {
8856  PendingIdentifierInfos[II].append(DeclIDs.begin(), DeclIDs.end());
8857  return;
8858  }
8859 
8860  for (unsigned I = 0, N = DeclIDs.size(); I != N; ++I) {
8861  if (!SemaObj) {
8862  // Queue this declaration so that it will be added to the
8863  // translation unit scope and identifier's declaration chain
8864  // once a Sema object is known.
8865  PreloadedDeclIDs.push_back(DeclIDs[I]);
8866  continue;
8867  }
8868 
8869  NamedDecl *D = cast<NamedDecl>(GetDecl(DeclIDs[I]));
8870 
8871  // If we're simply supposed to record the declarations, do so now.
8872  if (Decls) {
8873  Decls->push_back(D);
8874  continue;
8875  }
8876 
8877  // Introduce this declaration into the translation-unit scope
8878  // and add it to the declaration chain for this identifier, so
8879  // that (unqualified) name lookup will find it.
8880  pushExternalDeclIntoScope(D, II);
8881  }
8882 }
8883 
8884 IdentifierInfo *ASTReader::DecodeIdentifierInfo(IdentifierID ID) {
8885  if (ID == 0)
8886  return nullptr;
8887 
8888  if (IdentifiersLoaded.empty()) {
8889  Error("no identifier table in AST file");
8890  return nullptr;
8891  }
8892 
8893  ID -= 1;
8894  if (!IdentifiersLoaded[ID]) {
8895  GlobalIdentifierMapType::iterator I = GlobalIdentifierMap.find(ID + 1);
8896  assert(I != GlobalIdentifierMap.end() && "Corrupted global identifier map");
8897  ModuleFile *M = I->second;
8898  unsigned Index = ID - M->BaseIdentifierID;
8899  const unsigned char *Data =
8900  M->IdentifierTableData + M->IdentifierOffsets[Index];
8901 
8902  ASTIdentifierLookupTrait Trait(*this, *M);
8903  auto KeyDataLen = Trait.ReadKeyDataLength(Data);
8904  auto Key = Trait.ReadKey(Data, KeyDataLen.first);
8905  auto &II = PP.getIdentifierTable().get(Key);
8906  IdentifiersLoaded[ID] = &II;
8907  markIdentifierFromAST(*this, II);
8908  if (DeserializationListener)
8909  DeserializationListener->IdentifierRead(ID + 1, &II);
8910  }
8911 
8912  return IdentifiersLoaded[ID];
8913 }
8914 
8915 IdentifierInfo *ASTReader::getLocalIdentifier(ModuleFile &M, unsigned LocalID) {
8916  return DecodeIdentifierInfo(getGlobalIdentifierID(M, LocalID));
8917 }
8918 
8919 IdentifierID ASTReader::getGlobalIdentifierID(ModuleFile &M, unsigned LocalID) {
8920  if (LocalID < NUM_PREDEF_IDENT_IDS)
8921  return LocalID;
8922 
8923  if (!M.ModuleOffsetMap.empty())
8924  ReadModuleOffsetMap(M);
8925 
8926  ContinuousRangeMap<uint32_t, int, 2>::iterator I
8927  = M.IdentifierRemap.find(LocalID - NUM_PREDEF_IDENT_IDS);
8928  assert(I != M.IdentifierRemap.end()
8929  && "Invalid index into identifier index remap");
8930 
8931  return LocalID + I->second;
8932 }
8933 
8934 MacroInfo *ASTReader::getMacro(MacroID ID) {
8935  if (ID == 0)
8936  return nullptr;
8937 
8938  if (MacrosLoaded.empty()) {
8939  Error("no macro table in AST file");
8940  return nullptr;
8941  }
8942 
8943  ID -= NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS;
8944  if (!MacrosLoaded[ID]) {
8945  GlobalMacroMapType::iterator I
8946  = GlobalMacroMap.find(ID + NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS);
8947  assert(I != GlobalMacroMap.end() && "Corrupted global macro map");
8948  ModuleFile *M = I->second;
8949  unsigned Index = ID - M->BaseMacroID;
8950  MacrosLoaded[ID] =
8951  ReadMacroRecord(*M, M->MacroOffsetsBase + M->MacroOffsets[Index]);
8952 
8953  if (DeserializationListener)
8954  DeserializationListener->MacroRead(ID + NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS,
8955  MacrosLoaded[ID]);
8956  }
8957 
8958  return MacrosLoaded[ID];
8959 }
8960 
8961 MacroID ASTReader::getGlobalMacroID(ModuleFile &M, unsigned LocalID) {
8962  if (LocalID < NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS)
8963  return LocalID;
8964 
8965  if (!M.ModuleOffsetMap.empty())
8966  ReadModuleOffsetMap(M);
8967 
8968  ContinuousRangeMap<uint32_t, int, 2>::iterator I
8969  = M.MacroRemap.find(LocalID - NUM_PREDEF_MACRO_IDS);
8970  assert(I != M.MacroRemap.end() && "Invalid index into macro index remap");
8971 
8972  return LocalID + I->second;
8973 }

8991 Module *ASTReader::getSubmodule(SubmoduleID GlobalID) {
8992  if (GlobalID < NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS) {
8993  assert(GlobalID == 0 && "Unhandled global submodule ID");
8994  return nullptr;
8995  }
8996

8998  Error("submodule ID out of range in AST file");
8999  return nullptr;

9001 
9002  return SubmodulesLoaded[GlobalID - NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS];
9003 }

9009 ModuleFile *ASTReader::getLocalModuleFile(ModuleFile &M, unsigned ID) {
9010  if (ID & 1) {
9011  // It's a module, look it up by submodule ID.
9012  auto I = GlobalSubmoduleMap.find(getGlobalSubmoduleID(M, ID >> 1));
9013  return I == GlobalSubmoduleMap.end() ? nullptr : I->second;
9014  } else {
9015  // It's a prefix (preamble, PCH, ...). Look it up by index.
9016  unsigned IndexFromEnd = ID >> 1;
9017  assert(IndexFromEnd && "got reference to unknown module file");
9018  return getModuleManager().pch_modules().end()[-IndexFromEnd];
9019  }
9020 }
9021 
9022 unsigned ASTReader::getModuleFileID(ModuleFile *M) {
9023  if (!M)
9024  return 1;
9025 
9026  // For a file representing a module, use the submodule ID of the top-level
9027  // module as the file ID. For any other kind of file, the number of such
9028  // files loaded beforehand will be the same on reload.
9029  // FIXME: Is this true even if we have an explicit module file and a PCH?
9030  if (M->isModule())
9031  return ((M->BaseSubmoduleID + NUM_PREDEF_SUBMODULE_IDS) << 1) | 1;
9032 
9033  auto PCHModules = getModuleManager().pch_modules();
9034  auto I = llvm::find(PCHModules, M);
9035  assert(I != PCHModules.end() && "emitting reference to unknown file");
9036  return (I - PCHModules.end()) << 1;
9037 }
9038 
9039 std::optional<ASTSourceDescriptor> ASTReader::getSourceDescriptor(unsigned ID) {
9040  if (Module *M = getSubmodule(ID))
9041  return ASTSourceDescriptor(*M);
9042 
9043  // If there is only a single PCH, return it instead.
9044  // Chained PCH are not supported.
9045  const auto &PCHChain = ModuleMgr.pch_modules();
9046  if (std::distance(std::begin(PCHChain), std::end(PCHChain))) {
9047  ModuleFile &MF = ModuleMgr.getPrimaryModule();
9048  StringRef ModuleName = llvm::sys::path::filename(MF.OriginalSourceFileName);
9049  StringRef FileName = llvm::sys::path::filename(MF.FileName);
9050  return ASTSourceDescriptor(ModuleName,
9051  llvm::sys::path::parent_path(MF.FileName),
9052  FileName, MF.Signature);
9053  }
9054  return std::nullopt;
9055 }
9056 
9057 ExternalASTSource::ExtKind ASTReader::hasExternalDefinitions(const Decl *FD) {
9058  auto I = DefinitionSource.find(FD);
9059  if (I == DefinitionSource.end())
9060  return EK_ReplyHazy;
9061  return I->second ? EK_Never : EK_Always;
9062 }

9064 Selector ASTReader::getLocalSelector(ModuleFile &M, unsigned LocalID) {
9065  return DecodeSelector(getGlobalSelectorID(M, LocalID));
9066 }
9067 
9068 Selector ASTReader::DecodeSelector(serialization::SelectorID ID) {
9069  if (ID == 0)
9070  return Selector();
9071 
9072  if (ID > SelectorsLoaded.size()) {
9073  Error("selector ID out of range in AST file");
9074  return Selector();
9075  }
9076 
9077  if (SelectorsLoaded[ID - 1].getAsOpaquePtr() == nullptr) {
9078  // Load this selector from the selector table.
9079  GlobalSelectorMapType::iterator I = GlobalSelectorMap.find(ID);
9080  assert(I != GlobalSelectorMap.end() && "Corrupted global selector map");
9081  ModuleFile &M = *I->second;
9082  ASTSelectorLookupTrait Trait(*this, M);
9083  unsigned Idx = ID - M.BaseSelectorID - NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS;
9084  SelectorsLoaded[ID - 1] =
9085  Trait.ReadKey(M.SelectorLookupTableData + M.SelectorOffsets[Idx], 0);
9086  if (DeserializationListener)
9087  DeserializationListener->SelectorRead(ID, SelectorsLoaded[ID - 1]);
9088  }
9089 
9090  return SelectorsLoaded[ID - 1];
9091 }
9092 
9093 Selector ASTReader::GetExternalSelector(serialization::SelectorID ID) {
9094  return DecodeSelector(ID);
9095 }
9096 
9097 uint32_t ASTReader::GetNumExternalSelectors() {
9098  // ID 0 (the null selector) is considered an external selector.
9099  return getTotalNumSelectors() + 1;
9100 }
9101 
9102 serialization::SelectorID
9103 ASTReader::getGlobalSelectorID(ModuleFile &M, unsigned LocalID) const {
9104  if (LocalID < NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS)
9105  return LocalID;
9106 
9107  if (!M.ModuleOffsetMap.empty())
9108  ReadModuleOffsetMap(M);
9109 
9110  ContinuousRangeMap<uint32_t, int, 2>::iterator I
9111  = M.SelectorRemap.find(LocalID - NUM_PREDEF_SELECTOR_IDS);
9112  assert(I != M.SelectorRemap.end()
9113  && "Invalid index into selector index remap");
9114 
9115  return LocalID + I->second;
9116 }

9118 DeclarationNameLoc
9119 ASTRecordReader::readDeclarationNameLoc(DeclarationName Name) {
9120  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
9121  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
9122  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
9123  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
9124  return DeclarationNameLoc::makeNamedTypeLoc(readTypeSourceInfo());
9125 
9126  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
9127  return DeclarationNameLoc::makeCXXOperatorNameLoc(readSourceRange());
9128 
9129  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
9130  return DeclarationNameLoc::makeCXXLiteralOperatorNameLoc(
9131  readSourceLocation());
9132 
9133  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
9134  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
9135  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
9136  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
9137  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
9138  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
9139  break;
9140  }
9141  return DeclarationNameLoc();
9142 }

9156 void ASTRecordReader::readQualifierInfo(QualifierInfo &Info) {
9157  Info.QualifierLoc = readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
9158  unsigned NumTPLists = readInt();
9159  Info.NumTemplParamLists = NumTPLists;
9160  if (NumTPLists) {
9161  Info.TemplParamLists =
9162  new (getContext()) TemplateParameterList *[NumTPLists];
9163  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumTPLists; ++i)
9164  Info.TemplParamLists[i] = readTemplateParameterList();
9165  }
9166 }

9168 TemplateParameterList *
9169 ASTRecordReader::readTemplateParameterList() {
9170  SourceLocation TemplateLoc = readSourceLocation();
9171  SourceLocation LAngleLoc = readSourceLocation();
9172  SourceLocation RAngleLoc = readSourceLocation();
9173 
9174  unsigned NumParams = readInt();
9175  SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 16> Params;
9176  Params.reserve(NumParams);
9177  while (NumParams--)
9178  Params.push_back(readDeclAs<NamedDecl>());
9179 
9180  bool HasRequiresClause = readBool();
9181  Expr *RequiresClause = HasRequiresClause ? readExpr() : nullptr;
9182 
9183  TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams = TemplateParameterList::Create(
9184  getContext(), TemplateLoc, LAngleLoc, Params, RAngleLoc, RequiresClause);
9185  return TemplateParams;
9186 }

9188 void ASTRecordReader::readTemplateArgumentList(
9189  SmallVectorImpl<TemplateArgument> &TemplArgs,
9190  bool Canonicalize) {

9192  TemplArgs.reserve(NumTemplateArgs);
9193  while (NumTemplateArgs--)
9194  TemplArgs.push_back(readTemplateArgument(Canonicalize));
9195 }

9197 /// Read a UnresolvedSet structure.
9198 void ASTRecordReader::readUnresolvedSet(LazyASTUnresolvedSet &Set) {
9199  unsigned NumDecls = readInt();
9200  Set.reserve(getContext(), NumDecls);
9201  while (NumDecls--) {
9202  GlobalDeclID ID = readDeclID();
9203  AccessSpecifier AS = (AccessSpecifier) readInt();
9204  Set.addLazyDecl(getContext(), ID.get(), AS);
9205  }
9206 }

9208 CXXBaseSpecifier
9209 ASTRecordReader::readCXXBaseSpecifier() {
9210  bool isVirtual = readBool();
9211  bool isBaseOfClass = readBool();
9212  AccessSpecifier AS = static_cast<AccessSpecifier>(readInt());
9213  bool inheritConstructors = readBool();
9214  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = readTypeSourceInfo();
9215  SourceRange Range = readSourceRange();
9216  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = readSourceLocation();
9217  CXXBaseSpecifier Result(Range, isVirtual, isBaseOfClass, AS, TInfo,
9218  EllipsisLoc);
9219  Result.setInheritConstructors(inheritConstructors);
9220  return Result;
9221 }
9222 
9223 CXXCtorInitializer **
9224 ASTRecordReader::readCXXCtorInitializers() {
9225  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
9226  unsigned NumInitializers = readInt();
9227  assert(NumInitializers && "wrote ctor initializers but have no inits");
9228  auto **CtorInitializers = new (Context) CXXCtorInitializer*[NumInitializers];
9229  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumInitializers; ++i) {
9230  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
9231  bool IsBaseVirtual = false;
9232  FieldDecl *Member = nullptr;
9233  IndirectFieldDecl *IndirectMember = nullptr;
9234 
9235  CtorInitializerType Type = (CtorInitializerType) readInt();
9236  switch (Type) {
9237  case CTOR_INITIALIZER_BASE:
9238  TInfo = readTypeSourceInfo();
9239  IsBaseVirtual = readBool();
9240  break;
9241 
9242  case CTOR_INITIALIZER_DELEGATING:
9243  TInfo = readTypeSourceInfo();
9244  break;
9245 
9246  case CTOR_INITIALIZER_MEMBER:
9247  Member = readDeclAs<FieldDecl>();
9248  break;
9249 
9250  case CTOR_INITIALIZER_INDIRECT_MEMBER:
9251  IndirectMember = readDeclAs<IndirectFieldDecl>();
9252  break;
9253  }
9254 
9255  SourceLocation MemberOrEllipsisLoc = readSourceLocation();
9256  Expr *Init = readExpr();
9257  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
9258  SourceLocation RParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
9259 
9260  CXXCtorInitializer *BOMInit;
9261  if (Type == CTOR_INITIALIZER_BASE)
9262  BOMInit = new (Context)
9263  CXXCtorInitializer(Context, TInfo, IsBaseVirtual, LParenLoc, Init,
9264  RParenLoc, MemberOrEllipsisLoc);
9265  else if (Type == CTOR_INITIALIZER_DELEGATING)
9266  BOMInit = new (Context)
9267  CXXCtorInitializer(Context, TInfo, LParenLoc, Init, RParenLoc);
9268  else if (Member)
9269  BOMInit = new (Context)
9270  CXXCtorInitializer(Context, Member, MemberOrEllipsisLoc, LParenLoc,
9271  Init, RParenLoc);
9272  else
9273  BOMInit = new (Context)
9274  CXXCtorInitializer(Context, IndirectMember, MemberOrEllipsisLoc,
9275  LParenLoc, Init, RParenLoc);
9276 
9277  if (/*IsWritten*/readBool()) {
9278  unsigned SourceOrder = readInt();
9279  BOMInit->setSourceOrder(SourceOrder);
9280  }
9281 
9282  CtorInitializers[i] = BOMInit;
9283  }
9284 
9285  return CtorInitializers;
9286 }
9287 
9288 NestedNameSpecifierLoc
9289 ASTRecordReader::readNestedNameSpecifierLoc() {
9290  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
9291  unsigned N = readInt();
9292  NestedNameSpecifierLocBuilder Builder;
9293  for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I) {
9294  auto Kind = readNestedNameSpecifierKind();
9295  switch (Kind) {
9296  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier: {
9297  IdentifierInfo *II = readIdentifier();
9298  SourceRange Range = readSourceRange();
9299  Builder.Extend(Context, II, Range.getBegin(), Range.getEnd());
9300  break;
9301  }
9302 
9303  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace: {
9304  NamespaceDecl *NS = readDeclAs<NamespaceDecl>();
9305  SourceRange Range = readSourceRange();
9306  Builder.Extend(Context, NS, Range.getBegin(), Range.getEnd());
9307  break;
9308  }
9309 
9310  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias: {
9311  NamespaceAliasDecl *Alias = readDeclAs<NamespaceAliasDecl>();
9312  SourceRange Range = readSourceRange();
9313  Builder.Extend(Context, Alias, Range.getBegin(), Range.getEnd());
9314  break;
9315  }
9316 
9317  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
9318  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate: {
9319  bool Template = readBool();
9320  TypeSourceInfo *T = readTypeSourceInfo();
9321  if (!T)
9322  return NestedNameSpecifierLoc();
9323  SourceLocation ColonColonLoc = readSourceLocation();
9324 
9325  // FIXME: 'template' keyword location not saved anywhere, so we fake it.
9326  Builder.Extend(Context,
9327  Template? T->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc() : SourceLocation(),
9328  T->getTypeLoc(), ColonColonLoc);
9329  break;
9330  }
9331 
9332  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global: {
9333  SourceLocation ColonColonLoc = readSourceLocation();
9334  Builder.MakeGlobal(Context, ColonColonLoc);
9335  break;
9336  }
9337 
9338  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super: {
9339  CXXRecordDecl *RD = readDeclAs<CXXRecordDecl>();
9340  SourceRange Range = readSourceRange();
9341  Builder.MakeSuper(Context, RD, Range.getBegin(), Range.getEnd());
9342  break;
9343  }
9344  }
9345  }
9346 
9347  return Builder.getWithLocInContext(Context);
9348 }
9349 
9350 SourceRange ASTReader::ReadSourceRange(ModuleFile &F, const RecordData &Record,
9351  unsigned &Idx, LocSeq *Seq) {
9352  SourceLocation beg = ReadSourceLocation(F, Record, Idx, Seq);
9353  SourceLocation end = ReadSourceLocation(F, Record, Idx, Seq);
9354  return SourceRange(beg, end);
9355 }
9356 
9357 llvm::BitVector ASTReader::ReadBitVector(const RecordData &Record,
9358  const StringRef Blob) {
9359  unsigned Count = Record[0];
9360  const char *Byte = Blob.data();
9361  llvm::BitVector Ret = llvm::BitVector(Count, false);
9362  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Count; ++Byte)
9363  for (unsigned Bit = 0; Bit < 8 && I < Count; ++Bit, ++I)
9364  if (*Byte & (1 << Bit))
9365  Ret[I] = true;
9366  return Ret;
9367 }

9397 VersionTuple ASTReader::ReadVersionTuple(const RecordData &Record,
9398  unsigned &Idx) {
9399  unsigned Major = Record[Idx++];
9400  unsigned Minor = Record[Idx++];
9401  unsigned Subminor = Record[Idx++];
9402  if (Minor == 0)
9403  return VersionTuple(Major);
9404  if (Subminor == 0)
9405  return VersionTuple(Major, Minor - 1);
9406  return VersionTuple(Major, Minor - 1, Subminor - 1);
9407 }
