9447 
9448 void ASTReader::ReadComments() {
9449  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
9450  std::vector<RawComment *> Comments;
9451  for (SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<BitstreamCursor,
9452  serialization::ModuleFile *>>::iterator
9453  I = CommentsCursors.begin(),
9454  E = CommentsCursors.end();
9455  I != E; ++I) {
9456  Comments.clear();
9457  BitstreamCursor &Cursor = I->first;
9458  serialization::ModuleFile &F = *I->second;
9459  SavedStreamPosition SavedPosition(Cursor);
9460 
9461  RecordData Record;
9462  while (true) {
9463  Expected<llvm::BitstreamEntry> MaybeEntry =
9464  Cursor.advanceSkippingSubblocks(
9465  BitstreamCursor::AF_DontPopBlockAtEnd);
9466  if (!MaybeEntry) {
9467  Error(MaybeEntry.takeError());
9468  return;
9469  }
9470  llvm::BitstreamEntry Entry = MaybeEntry.get();
9471 
9472  switch (Entry.Kind) {
9473  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
9474  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::Error:
9475  Error("malformed block record in AST file");
9476  return;
9477  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
9478  goto NextCursor;
9479  case llvm::BitstreamEntry::Record:
9480  // The interesting case.
9481  break;
9482  }
9483 
9484  // Read a record.
9485  Record.clear();
9486  Expected<unsigned> MaybeComment = Cursor.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
9487  if (!MaybeComment) {
9488  Error(MaybeComment.takeError());
9489  return;
9490  }
9491  switch ((CommentRecordTypes)MaybeComment.get()) {
9492  case COMMENTS_RAW_COMMENT: {
9493  unsigned Idx = 0;
9494  SourceRange SR = ReadSourceRange(F, Record, Idx);
9495  RawComment::CommentKind Kind =
9496  (RawComment::CommentKind) Record[Idx++];
9497  bool IsTrailingComment = Record[Idx++];
9498  bool IsAlmostTrailingComment = Record[Idx++];
9499  Comments.push_back(new (Context) RawComment(
9500  SR, Kind, IsTrailingComment, IsAlmostTrailingComment));
9501  break;
9502  }
9503  }
9504  }
9505  NextCursor:
9506  llvm::DenseMap<FileID, std::map<unsigned, RawComment *>>
9507  FileToOffsetToComment;
9508  for (RawComment *C : Comments) {
9509  SourceLocation CommentLoc = C->getBeginLoc();
9510  if (CommentLoc.isValid()) {
9511  std::pair<FileID, unsigned> Loc =
9512  SourceMgr.getDecomposedLoc(CommentLoc);
9513  if (Loc.first.isValid())
9514  Context.Comments.OrderedComments[Loc.first].emplace(Loc.second, C);
9515  }
9516  }
9517  }
9518 }
9519 
9520 void ASTReader::visitInputFileInfos(
9521  serialization::ModuleFile &MF, bool IncludeSystem,
9522  llvm::function_ref<void(const serialization::InputFileInfo &IFI,
9523  bool IsSystem)>
9524  Visitor) {
9525  unsigned NumUserInputs = MF.NumUserInputFiles;
9526  unsigned NumInputs = MF.InputFilesLoaded.size();
9527  assert(NumUserInputs <= NumInputs);
9528  unsigned N = IncludeSystem ? NumInputs : NumUserInputs;
9529  for (unsigned I = 0; I < N; ++I) {
9530  bool IsSystem = I >= NumUserInputs;
9531  InputFileInfo IFI = getInputFileInfo(MF, I+1);
9532  Visitor(IFI, IsSystem);
9533  }
9534 }
9535 
9536 void ASTReader::visitInputFiles(serialization::ModuleFile &MF,
9537  bool IncludeSystem, bool Complain,
9538  llvm::function_ref<void(const serialization::InputFile &IF,
9539  bool isSystem)> Visitor) {
9540  unsigned NumUserInputs = MF.NumUserInputFiles;
9541  unsigned NumInputs = MF.InputFilesLoaded.size();
9542  assert(NumUserInputs <= NumInputs);
9543  unsigned N = IncludeSystem ? NumInputs : NumUserInputs;
9544  for (unsigned I = 0; I < N; ++I) {
9545  bool IsSystem = I >= NumUserInputs;
9546  InputFile IF = getInputFile(MF, I+1, Complain);
9547  Visitor(IF, IsSystem);
9548  }
9549 }
9550 
9551 void ASTReader::visitTopLevelModuleMaps(
9552  serialization::ModuleFile &MF,
9553  llvm::function_ref<void(FileEntryRef FE)> Visitor) {
9554  unsigned NumInputs = MF.InputFilesLoaded.size();
9555  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumInputs; ++I) {
9556  InputFileInfo IFI = getInputFileInfo(MF, I + 1);
9557  if (IFI.TopLevel && IFI.ModuleMap)
9558  if (auto FE = getInputFile(MF, I + 1).getFile())
9559  Visitor(*FE);
9560  }
9561 }
9562 
9563 void ASTReader::finishPendingActions() {
9564  while (
9565  !PendingIdentifierInfos.empty() || !PendingDeducedFunctionTypes.empty() ||
9566  !PendingDeducedVarTypes.empty() || !PendingIncompleteDeclChains.empty() ||
9567  !PendingDeclChains.empty() || !PendingMacroIDs.empty() ||
9568  !PendingDeclContextInfos.empty() || !PendingUpdateRecords.empty() ||
9569  !PendingObjCExtensionIvarRedeclarations.empty()) {
9570  // If any identifiers with corresponding top-level declarations have
9571  // been loaded, load those declarations now.
9572  using TopLevelDeclsMap =
9573  llvm::DenseMap<IdentifierInfo *, SmallVector<Decl *, 2>>;
9574  TopLevelDeclsMap TopLevelDecls;
9575 
9576  while (!PendingIdentifierInfos.empty()) {
9577  IdentifierInfo *II = PendingIdentifierInfos.back().first;
9578  SmallVector<GlobalDeclID, 4> DeclIDs =
9579  std::move(PendingIdentifierInfos.back().second);
9580  PendingIdentifierInfos.pop_back();
9581 
9582  SetGloballyVisibleDecls(II, DeclIDs, &TopLevelDecls[II]);
9583  }
9584 
9585  // Load each function type that we deferred loading because it was a
9586  // deduced type that might refer to a local type declared within itself.
9587  for (unsigned I = 0; I != PendingDeducedFunctionTypes.size(); ++I) {
9588  auto *FD = PendingDeducedFunctionTypes[I].first;
9589  FD->setType(GetType(PendingDeducedFunctionTypes[I].second));
9590 
9591  if (auto *DT = FD->getReturnType()->getContainedDeducedType()) {
9592  // If we gave a function a deduced return type, remember that we need to
9593  // propagate that along the redeclaration chain.
9594  if (DT->isDeduced()) {
9595  PendingDeducedTypeUpdates.insert(
9596  {FD->getCanonicalDecl(), FD->getReturnType()});
9597  continue;
9598  }
9599 
9600  // The function has undeduced DeduceType return type. We hope we can
9601  // find the deduced type by iterating the redecls in other modules
9602  // later.
9603  PendingUndeducedFunctionDecls.push_back(FD);
9604  continue;
9605  }
9606  }
9607  PendingDeducedFunctionTypes.clear();
9608 
9609  // Load each variable type that we deferred loading because it was a
9610  // deduced type that might refer to a local type declared within itself.
9611  for (unsigned I = 0; I != PendingDeducedVarTypes.size(); ++I) {
9612  auto *VD = PendingDeducedVarTypes[I].first;
9613  VD->setType(GetType(PendingDeducedVarTypes[I].second));
9614  }
9615  PendingDeducedVarTypes.clear();
9616 
9617  // For each decl chain that we wanted to complete while deserializing, mark
9618  // it as "still needs to be completed".
9619  for (unsigned I = 0; I != PendingIncompleteDeclChains.size(); ++I) {
9620  markIncompleteDeclChain(PendingIncompleteDeclChains[I]);
9621  }
9622  PendingIncompleteDeclChains.clear();
9623 
9624  // Load pending declaration chains.
9625  for (unsigned I = 0; I != PendingDeclChains.size(); ++I)
9626  loadPendingDeclChain(PendingDeclChains[I].first,
9627  PendingDeclChains[I].second);
9628  PendingDeclChains.clear();
9629 
9630  // Make the most recent of the top-level declarations visible.
9631  for (TopLevelDeclsMap::iterator TLD = TopLevelDecls.begin(),
9632  TLDEnd = TopLevelDecls.end(); TLD != TLDEnd; ++TLD) {
9633  IdentifierInfo *II = TLD->first;
9634  for (unsigned I = 0, N = TLD->second.size(); I != N; ++I) {
9635  pushExternalDeclIntoScope(cast<NamedDecl>(TLD->second[I]), II);
9636  }
9637  }
9638 
9639  // Load any pending macro definitions.
9640  for (unsigned I = 0; I != PendingMacroIDs.size(); ++I) {
9641  IdentifierInfo *II = PendingMacroIDs.begin()[I].first;
9642  SmallVector<PendingMacroInfo, 2> GlobalIDs;
9643  GlobalIDs.swap(PendingMacroIDs.begin()[I].second);
9644  // Initialize the macro history from chained-PCHs ahead of module imports.
9645  for (unsigned IDIdx = 0, NumIDs = GlobalIDs.size(); IDIdx != NumIDs;
9646  ++IDIdx) {
9647  const PendingMacroInfo &Info = GlobalIDs[IDIdx];
9648  if (!Info.M->isModule())
9649  resolvePendingMacro(II, Info);
9650  }
9651  // Handle module imports.
9652  for (unsigned IDIdx = 0, NumIDs = GlobalIDs.size(); IDIdx != NumIDs;
9653  ++IDIdx) {
9654  const PendingMacroInfo &Info = GlobalIDs[IDIdx];
9655  if (Info.M->isModule())
9656  resolvePendingMacro(II, Info);
9657  }
9658  }
9659  PendingMacroIDs.clear();
9660 
9661  // Wire up the DeclContexts for Decls that we delayed setting until
9662  // recursive loading is completed.
9663  while (!PendingDeclContextInfos.empty()) {
9664  PendingDeclContextInfo Info = PendingDeclContextInfos.front();
9665  PendingDeclContextInfos.pop_front();
9666  DeclContext *SemaDC = cast<DeclContext>(GetDecl(Info.SemaDC));
9667  DeclContext *LexicalDC = cast<DeclContext>(GetDecl(Info.LexicalDC));
9668  Info.D->setDeclContextsImpl(SemaDC, LexicalDC, getContext());
9669  }
9670 
9671  // Perform any pending declaration updates.
9672  while (!PendingUpdateRecords.empty()) {
9673  auto Update = PendingUpdateRecords.pop_back_val();
9674  ReadingKindTracker ReadingKind(Read_Decl, *this);
9675  loadDeclUpdateRecords(Update);
9676  }
9677 
9678  while (!PendingObjCExtensionIvarRedeclarations.empty()) {
9679  auto ExtensionsPair = PendingObjCExtensionIvarRedeclarations.back().first;
9680  auto DuplicateIvars =
9681  PendingObjCExtensionIvarRedeclarations.back().second;
9682  llvm::DenseSet<std::pair<Decl *, Decl *>> NonEquivalentDecls;
9683  StructuralEquivalenceContext Ctx(
9684  ExtensionsPair.first->getASTContext(),
9685  ExtensionsPair.second->getASTContext(), NonEquivalentDecls,
9686  StructuralEquivalenceKind::Default, /*StrictTypeSpelling =*/false,
9687  /*Complain =*/false,
9688  /*ErrorOnTagTypeMismatch =*/true);
9689  if (Ctx.IsEquivalent(ExtensionsPair.first, ExtensionsPair.second)) {
9690  // Merge redeclared ivars with their predecessors.
9691  for (auto IvarPair : DuplicateIvars) {
9692  ObjCIvarDecl *Ivar = IvarPair.first, *PrevIvar = IvarPair.second;
9693  // Change semantic DeclContext but keep the lexical one.
9694  Ivar->setDeclContextsImpl(PrevIvar->getDeclContext(),
9695  Ivar->getLexicalDeclContext(),
9696  getContext());
9697  getContext().setPrimaryMergedDecl(Ivar, PrevIvar->getCanonicalDecl());
9698  }
9699  // Invalidate duplicate extension and the cached ivar list.
9700  ExtensionsPair.first->setInvalidDecl();
9701  ExtensionsPair.second->getClassInterface()
9702  ->getDefinition()
9703  ->setIvarList(nullptr);
9704  } else {
9705  for (auto IvarPair : DuplicateIvars) {
9706  Diag(IvarPair.first->getLocation(),
9707  diag::err_duplicate_ivar_declaration)
9708  << IvarPair.first->getIdentifier();
9709  Diag(IvarPair.second->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_definition);
9710  }
9711  }
9712  PendingObjCExtensionIvarRedeclarations.pop_back();
9713  }
9714  }
9715 
9716  // At this point, all update records for loaded decls are in place, so any
9717  // fake class definitions should have become real.
9718  assert(PendingFakeDefinitionData.empty() &&
9719  "faked up a class definition but never saw the real one");
9720 
9721  // If we deserialized any C++ or Objective-C class definitions, any
9722  // Objective-C protocol definitions, or any redeclarable templates, make sure
9723  // that all redeclarations point to the definitions. Note that this can only
9724  // happen now, after the redeclaration chains have been fully wired.
9725  for (Decl *D : PendingDefinitions) {
9726  if (TagDecl *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
9727  if (const TagType *TagT = dyn_cast<TagType>(TD->getTypeForDecl())) {
9728  // Make sure that the TagType points at the definition.
9729  const_cast<TagType*>(TagT)->decl = TD;
9730  }
9731 
9732  if (auto RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
9733  for (auto *R = getMostRecentExistingDecl(RD); R;
9734  R = R->getPreviousDecl()) {
9735  assert((R == D) ==
9736  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(R)->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
9737  "declaration thinks it's the definition but it isn't");
9738  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(R)->DefinitionData = RD->DefinitionData;
9739  }
9740  }
9741 
9742  continue;
9743  }
9744 
9745  if (auto ID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D)) {
9746  // Make sure that the ObjCInterfaceType points at the definition.
9747  const_cast<ObjCInterfaceType *>(cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(ID->TypeForDecl))
9748  ->Decl = ID;
9749 
9750  for (auto *R = getMostRecentExistingDecl(ID); R; R = R->getPreviousDecl())
9751  cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(R)->Data = ID->Data;
9752 
9753  continue;
9754  }
9755 
9756  if (auto PD = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D)) {
9757  for (auto *R = getMostRecentExistingDecl(PD); R; R = R->getPreviousDecl())
9758  cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(R)->Data = PD->Data;
9759 
9760  continue;
9761  }
9762 
9763  auto RTD = cast<RedeclarableTemplateDecl>(D)->getCanonicalDecl();
9764  for (auto *R = getMostRecentExistingDecl(RTD); R; R = R->getPreviousDecl())
9765  cast<RedeclarableTemplateDecl>(R)->Common = RTD->Common;
9766  }
9767  PendingDefinitions.clear();
9768 
9769  // Load the bodies of any functions or methods we've encountered. We do
9770  // this now (delayed) so that we can be sure that the declaration chains
9771  // have been fully wired up (hasBody relies on this).
9772  // FIXME: We shouldn't require complete redeclaration chains here.
9773  for (PendingBodiesMap::iterator PB = PendingBodies.begin(),
9774  PBEnd = PendingBodies.end();
9775  PB != PBEnd; ++PB) {
9776  if (FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(PB->first)) {
9777  // For a function defined inline within a class template, force the
9778  // canonical definition to be the one inside the canonical definition of
9779  // the template. This ensures that we instantiate from a correct view
9780  // of the template.
9781  //
9782  // Sadly we can't do this more generally: we can't be sure that all
9783  // copies of an arbitrary class definition will have the same members
9784  // defined (eg, some member functions may not be instantiated, and some
9785  // special members may or may not have been implicitly defined).
9786  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getLexicalParent()))
9787  if (RD->isDependentContext() && !RD->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
9788  continue;
9789 
9790  // FIXME: Check for =delete/=default?
9791  const FunctionDecl *Defn = nullptr;
9792  if (!getContext().getLangOpts().Modules || !FD->hasBody(Defn)) {
9793  FD->setLazyBody(PB->second);
9794  } else {
9795  auto *NonConstDefn = const_cast<FunctionDecl*>(Defn);
9796  mergeDefinitionVisibility(NonConstDefn, FD);
9797 
9798  if (!FD->isLateTemplateParsed() &&
9799  !NonConstDefn->isLateTemplateParsed() &&
9800  // We only perform ODR checks for decls not in the explicit
9801  // global module fragment.
9802  !shouldSkipCheckingODR(FD) &&
9803  FD->getODRHash() != NonConstDefn->getODRHash()) {
9804  if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
9805  PendingFunctionOdrMergeFailures[FD].push_back(NonConstDefn);
9806  } else if (FD->getLexicalParent()->isFileContext() &&
9807  NonConstDefn->getLexicalParent()->isFileContext()) {
9808  // Only diagnose out-of-line method definitions. If they are
9809  // in class definitions, then an error will be generated when
9810  // processing the class bodies.
9811  PendingFunctionOdrMergeFailures[FD].push_back(NonConstDefn);
9812  }
9813  }
9814  }
9815  continue;
9816  }
9817 
9818  ObjCMethodDecl *MD = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(PB->first);
9819  if (!getContext().getLangOpts().Modules || !MD->hasBody())
9820  MD->setLazyBody(PB->second);
9821  }
9822  PendingBodies.clear();
9823 
9824  // Inform any classes that had members added that they now have more members.
9825  for (auto [RD, MD] : PendingAddedClassMembers) {
9826  RD->addedMember(MD);
9827  }
9828  PendingAddedClassMembers.clear();
9829 
9830  // Do some cleanup.
9831  for (auto *ND : PendingMergedDefinitionsToDeduplicate)
9832  getContext().deduplicateMergedDefinitonsFor(ND);
9833  PendingMergedDefinitionsToDeduplicate.clear();
9834 }
9835 
9836 void ASTReader::diagnoseOdrViolations() {
9837  if (PendingOdrMergeFailures.empty() && PendingOdrMergeChecks.empty() &&
9838  PendingRecordOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
9839  PendingFunctionOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
9840  PendingEnumOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
9841  PendingObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
9842  PendingObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures.empty())
9843  return;
9844 
9845  // Trigger the import of the full definition of each class that had any
9846  // odr-merging problems, so we can produce better diagnostics for them.
9847  // These updates may in turn find and diagnose some ODR failures, so take
9848  // ownership of the set first.
9849  auto OdrMergeFailures = std::move(PendingOdrMergeFailures);
9850  PendingOdrMergeFailures.clear();
9851  for (auto &Merge : OdrMergeFailures) {
9852  Merge.first->buildLookup();
9853  Merge.first->decls_begin();
9854  Merge.first->bases_begin();
9855  Merge.first->vbases_begin();
9856  for (auto &RecordPair : Merge.second) {
9857  auto *RD = RecordPair.first;
9858  RD->decls_begin();
9859  RD->bases_begin();
9860  RD->vbases_begin();
9861  }
9862  }
9863 
9864  // Trigger the import of the full definition of each record in C/ObjC.
9865  auto RecordOdrMergeFailures = std::move(PendingRecordOdrMergeFailures);
9866  PendingRecordOdrMergeFailures.clear();
9867  for (auto &Merge : RecordOdrMergeFailures) {
9868  Merge.first->decls_begin();
9869  for (auto &D : Merge.second)
9870  D->decls_begin();
9871  }
9872 
9873  // Trigger the import of the full interface definition.
9874  auto ObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures =
9875  std::move(PendingObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures);
9876  PendingObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures.clear();
9877  for (auto &Merge : ObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures) {
9878  Merge.first->decls_begin();
9879  for (auto &InterfacePair : Merge.second)
9880  InterfacePair.first->decls_begin();
9881  }
9882 
9883  // Trigger the import of functions.
9884  auto FunctionOdrMergeFailures = std::move(PendingFunctionOdrMergeFailures);
9885  PendingFunctionOdrMergeFailures.clear();
9886  for (auto &Merge : FunctionOdrMergeFailures) {
9887  Merge.first->buildLookup();
9888  Merge.first->decls_begin();
9889  Merge.first->getBody();
9890  for (auto &FD : Merge.second) {
9891  FD->buildLookup();
9892  FD->decls_begin();
9893  FD->getBody();
9894  }
9895  }
9896 
9897  // Trigger the import of enums.
9898  auto EnumOdrMergeFailures = std::move(PendingEnumOdrMergeFailures);
9899  PendingEnumOdrMergeFailures.clear();
9900  for (auto &Merge : EnumOdrMergeFailures) {
9901  Merge.first->decls_begin();
9902  for (auto &Enum : Merge.second) {
9903  Enum->decls_begin();
9904  }
9905  }
9906 
9907  // Trigger the import of the full protocol definition.
9908  auto ObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures =
9909  std::move(PendingObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures);
9910  PendingObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures.clear();
9911  for (auto &Merge : ObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures) {
9912  Merge.first->decls_begin();
9913  for (auto &ProtocolPair : Merge.second)
9914  ProtocolPair.first->decls_begin();
9915  }
9916 
9917  // For each declaration from a merged context, check that the canonical
9918  // definition of that context also contains a declaration of the same
9919  // entity.
9920  //
9921  // Caution: this loop does things that might invalidate iterators into
9922  // PendingOdrMergeChecks. Don't turn this into a range-based for loop!
9923  while (!PendingOdrMergeChecks.empty()) {
9924  NamedDecl *D = PendingOdrMergeChecks.pop_back_val();
9925 
9926  // FIXME: Skip over implicit declarations for now. This matters for things
9927  // like implicitly-declared special member functions. This isn't entirely
9928  // correct; we can end up with multiple unmerged declarations of the same
9929  // implicit entity.
9930  if (D->isImplicit())
9931  continue;
9932 
9933  DeclContext *CanonDef = D->getDeclContext();
9934 
9935  bool Found = false;
9936  const Decl *DCanon = D->getCanonicalDecl();
9937 
9938  for (auto *RI : D->redecls()) {
9939  if (RI->getLexicalDeclContext() == CanonDef) {
9940  Found = true;
9941  break;
9942  }
9943  }
9944  if (Found)
9945  continue;
9946 
9947  // Quick check failed, time to do the slow thing. Note, we can't just
9948  // look up the name of D in CanonDef here, because the member that is
9949  // in CanonDef might not be found by name lookup (it might have been
9950  // replaced by a more recent declaration in the lookup table), and we
9951  // can't necessarily find it in the redeclaration chain because it might
9952  // be merely mergeable, not redeclarable.
9953  llvm::SmallVector<const NamedDecl*, 4> Candidates;
9954  for (auto *CanonMember : CanonDef->decls()) {
9955  if (CanonMember->getCanonicalDecl() == DCanon) {
9956  // This can happen if the declaration is merely mergeable and not
9957  // actually redeclarable (we looked for redeclarations earlier).
9958  //
9959  // FIXME: We should be able to detect this more efficiently, without
9960  // pulling in all of the members of CanonDef.
9961  Found = true;
9962  break;
9963  }
9964  if (auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(CanonMember))
9965  if (ND->getDeclName() == D->getDeclName())
9966  Candidates.push_back(ND);
9967  }
9968 
9969  if (!Found) {
9970  // The AST doesn't like TagDecls becoming invalid after they've been
9971  // completed. We only really need to mark FieldDecls as invalid here.
9972  if (!isa<TagDecl>(D))
9973  D->setInvalidDecl();
9974 
9975  // Ensure we don't accidentally recursively enter deserialization while
9976  // we're producing our diagnostic.
9977  Deserializing RecursionGuard(this);
9978 
9979  std::string CanonDefModule =
9980  ODRDiagsEmitter::getOwningModuleNameForDiagnostic(
9981  cast<Decl>(CanonDef));
9982  Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_module_odr_violation_missing_decl)
9983  << D << ODRDiagsEmitter::getOwningModuleNameForDiagnostic(D)
9984  << CanonDef << CanonDefModule.empty() << CanonDefModule;
9985 
9986  if (Candidates.empty())
9987  Diag(cast<Decl>(CanonDef)->getLocation(),
9988  diag::note_module_odr_violation_no_possible_decls) << D;
9989  else {
9990  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Candidates.size(); I != N; ++I)
9991  Diag(Candidates[I]->getLocation(),
9992  diag::note_module_odr_violation_possible_decl)
9993  << Candidates[I];
9994  }
9995 
9996  DiagnosedOdrMergeFailures.insert(CanonDef);
9997  }
9998  }
9999 
10000  if (OdrMergeFailures.empty() && RecordOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
10001  FunctionOdrMergeFailures.empty() && EnumOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
10002  ObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures.empty() &&
10003  ObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures.empty())
10004  return;
10005 
10006  ODRDiagsEmitter DiagsEmitter(Diags, getContext(),
10007  getPreprocessor().getLangOpts());
10008 
10009  // Issue any pending ODR-failure diagnostics.
10010  for (auto &Merge : OdrMergeFailures) {
10011  // If we've already pointed out a specific problem with this class, don't
10012  // bother issuing a general "something's different" diagnostic.
10013  if (!DiagnosedOdrMergeFailures.insert(Merge.first).second)
10014  continue;
10015 
10016  bool Diagnosed = false;
10017  CXXRecordDecl *FirstRecord = Merge.first;
10018  for (auto &RecordPair : Merge.second) {
10019  if (DiagsEmitter.diagnoseMismatch(FirstRecord, RecordPair.first,
10020  RecordPair.second)) {
10021  Diagnosed = true;
10022  break;
10023  }
10024  }
10025 
10026  if (!Diagnosed) {
10027  // All definitions are updates to the same declaration. This happens if a
10028  // module instantiates the declaration of a class template specialization
10029  // and two or more other modules instantiate its definition.
10030  //
10031  // FIXME: Indicate which modules had instantiations of this definition.
10032  // FIXME: How can this even happen?
10033  Diag(Merge.first->getLocation(),
10034  diag::err_module_odr_violation_different_instantiations)
10035  << Merge.first;
10036  }
10037  }
10038 
10039  // Issue any pending ODR-failure diagnostics for RecordDecl in C/ObjC. Note
10040  // that in C++ this is done as a part of CXXRecordDecl ODR checking.
10041  for (auto &Merge : RecordOdrMergeFailures) {
10042  // If we've already pointed out a specific problem with this class, don't
10043  // bother issuing a general "something's different" diagnostic.
10044  if (!DiagnosedOdrMergeFailures.insert(Merge.first).second)
10045  continue;
10046 
10047  RecordDecl *FirstRecord = Merge.first;
10048  bool Diagnosed = false;
10049  for (auto *SecondRecord : Merge.second) {
10050  if (DiagsEmitter.diagnoseMismatch(FirstRecord, SecondRecord)) {
10051  Diagnosed = true;
10052  break;
10053  }
10054  }
10055  (void)Diagnosed;
10056  assert(Diagnosed && "Unable to emit ODR diagnostic.");
10057  }
10058 
10059  // Issue ODR failures diagnostics for functions.
10060  for (auto &Merge : FunctionOdrMergeFailures) {
10061  FunctionDecl *FirstFunction = Merge.first;
10062  bool Diagnosed = false;
10063  for (auto &SecondFunction : Merge.second) {
10064  if (DiagsEmitter.diagnoseMismatch(FirstFunction, SecondFunction)) {
10065  Diagnosed = true;
10066  break;
10067  }
10068  }
10069  (void)Diagnosed;
10070  assert(Diagnosed && "Unable to emit ODR diagnostic.");
10071  }
10072 
10073  // Issue ODR failures diagnostics for enums.
10074  for (auto &Merge : EnumOdrMergeFailures) {
10075  // If we've already pointed out a specific problem with this enum, don't
10076  // bother issuing a general "something's different" diagnostic.
10077  if (!DiagnosedOdrMergeFailures.insert(Merge.first).second)
10078  continue;
10079 
10080  EnumDecl *FirstEnum = Merge.first;
10081  bool Diagnosed = false;
10082  for (auto &SecondEnum : Merge.second) {
10083  if (DiagsEmitter.diagnoseMismatch(FirstEnum, SecondEnum)) {
10084  Diagnosed = true;
10085  break;
10086  }
10087  }
10088  (void)Diagnosed;
10089  assert(Diagnosed && "Unable to emit ODR diagnostic.");
10090  }
10091 
10092  for (auto &Merge : ObjCInterfaceOdrMergeFailures) {
10093  // If we've already pointed out a specific problem with this interface,
10094  // don't bother issuing a general "something's different" diagnostic.
10095  if (!DiagnosedOdrMergeFailures.insert(Merge.first).second)
10096  continue;
10097 
10098  bool Diagnosed = false;
10099  ObjCInterfaceDecl *FirstID = Merge.first;
10100  for (auto &InterfacePair : Merge.second) {
10101  if (DiagsEmitter.diagnoseMismatch(FirstID, InterfacePair.first,
10102  InterfacePair.second)) {
10103  Diagnosed = true;
10104  break;
10105  }
10106  }
10107  (void)Diagnosed;
10108  assert(Diagnosed && "Unable to emit ODR diagnostic.");
10109  }
10110 
10111  for (auto &Merge : ObjCProtocolOdrMergeFailures) {
10112  // If we've already pointed out a specific problem with this protocol,
10113  // don't bother issuing a general "something's different" diagnostic.
10114  if (!DiagnosedOdrMergeFailures.insert(Merge.first).second)
10115  continue;
10116 
10117  ObjCProtocolDecl *FirstProtocol = Merge.first;
10118  bool Diagnosed = false;
10119  for (auto &ProtocolPair : Merge.second) {
10120  if (DiagsEmitter.diagnoseMismatch(FirstProtocol, ProtocolPair.first,
10121  ProtocolPair.second)) {
10122  Diagnosed = true;
10123  break;
10124  }
10125  }
10126  (void)Diagnosed;
10127  assert(Diagnosed && "Unable to emit ODR diagnostic.");
10128  }
10129 }
10130 
10131 void ASTReader::StartedDeserializing() {
10132  if (++NumCurrentElementsDeserializing == 1 && ReadTimer.get())
10133  ReadTimer->startTimer();
10134 }
10135 
10136 void ASTReader::FinishedDeserializing() {
10137  assert(NumCurrentElementsDeserializing &&
10138  "FinishedDeserializing not paired with StartedDeserializing");
10139  if (NumCurrentElementsDeserializing == 1) {
10140  // We decrease NumCurrentElementsDeserializing only after pending actions
10141  // are finished, to avoid recursively re-calling finishPendingActions().
10142  finishPendingActions();
10143  }
10144  --NumCurrentElementsDeserializing;
10145 
10146  if (NumCurrentElementsDeserializing == 0) {
10147  // Propagate exception specification and deduced type updates along
10148  // redeclaration chains.
10149  //
10150  // We do this now rather than in finishPendingActions because we want to
10151  // be able to walk the complete redeclaration chains of the updated decls.
10152  while (!PendingExceptionSpecUpdates.empty() ||
10153  !PendingDeducedTypeUpdates.empty()) {
10154  auto ESUpdates = std::move(PendingExceptionSpecUpdates);
10155  PendingExceptionSpecUpdates.clear();
10156  for (auto Update : ESUpdates) {
10157  ProcessingUpdatesRAIIObj ProcessingUpdates(*this);
10158  auto *FPT = Update.second->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
10159  auto ESI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo().ExceptionSpec;
10160  if (auto *Listener = getContext().getASTMutationListener())
10161  Listener->ResolvedExceptionSpec(cast<FunctionDecl>(Update.second));
10162  for (auto *Redecl : Update.second->redecls())
10163  getContext().adjustExceptionSpec(cast<FunctionDecl>(Redecl), ESI);
10164  }
10165 
10166  auto DTUpdates = std::move(PendingDeducedTypeUpdates);
10167  PendingDeducedTypeUpdates.clear();
10168  for (auto Update : DTUpdates) {
10169  ProcessingUpdatesRAIIObj ProcessingUpdates(*this);
10170  // FIXME: If the return type is already deduced, check that it matches.
10171  getContext().adjustDeducedFunctionResultType(Update.first,
10172  Update.second);
10173  }
10174 
10175  auto UDTUpdates = std::move(PendingUndeducedFunctionDecls);
10176  PendingUndeducedFunctionDecls.clear();
10177  // We hope we can find the deduced type for the functions by iterating
10178  // redeclarations in other modules.
10179  for (FunctionDecl *UndeducedFD : UDTUpdates)
10180  (void)UndeducedFD->getMostRecentDecl();
10181  }
10182 
10183  if (ReadTimer)
10184  ReadTimer->stopTimer();
10185 
10186  diagnoseOdrViolations();
10187 
10188  // We are not in recursive loading, so it's safe to pass the "interesting"
10189  // decls to the consumer.
10190  if (Consumer)
10191  PassInterestingDeclsToConsumer();
10192  }
10193 }
10194 
10195 void ASTReader::pushExternalDeclIntoScope(NamedDecl *D, DeclarationName Name) {
10196  if (const IdentifierInfo *II = Name.getAsIdentifierInfo()) {
10197  // Remove any fake results before adding any real ones.
10198  auto It = PendingFakeLookupResults.find(II);
10199  if (It != PendingFakeLookupResults.end()) {
10200  for (auto *ND : It->second)
10201  SemaObj->IdResolver.RemoveDecl(ND);
10202  // FIXME: this works around module+PCH performance issue.
10203  // Rather than erase the result from the map, which is O(n), just clear
10204  // the vector of NamedDecls.
10205  It->second.clear();
10206  }
10207  }
10208 
10209  if (SemaObj->IdResolver.tryAddTopLevelDecl(D, Name) && SemaObj->TUScope) {
10210  SemaObj->TUScope->AddDecl(D);
10211  } else if (SemaObj->TUScope) {
10212  // Adding the decl to IdResolver may have failed because it was already in
10213  // (even though it was not added in scope). If it is already in, make sure
10214  // it gets in the scope as well.
10215  if (llvm::is_contained(SemaObj->IdResolver.decls(Name), D))
10216  SemaObj->TUScope->AddDecl(D);
10217  }
10218 }
10219 
10220 ASTReader::ASTReader(Preprocessor &PP, InMemoryModuleCache &ModuleCache,
10221  ASTContext *Context,
10222  const PCHContainerReader &PCHContainerRdr,
10223  ArrayRef<std::shared_ptr<ModuleFileExtension>> Extensions,
10224  StringRef isysroot,
10225  DisableValidationForModuleKind DisableValidationKind,
10226  bool AllowASTWithCompilerErrors,
10227  bool AllowConfigurationMismatch, bool ValidateSystemInputs,
10228  bool ValidateASTInputFilesContent, bool UseGlobalIndex,
10229  std::unique_ptr<llvm::Timer> ReadTimer)
10230  : Listener(bool(DisableValidationKind &DisableValidationForModuleKind::PCH)
10231  ? cast<ASTReaderListener>(new SimpleASTReaderListener(PP))
10232  : cast<ASTReaderListener>(new PCHValidator(PP, *this))),
10233  SourceMgr(PP.getSourceManager()), FileMgr(PP.getFileManager()),
10234  PCHContainerRdr(PCHContainerRdr), Diags(PP.getDiagnostics()), PP(PP),
10235  ContextObj(Context), ModuleMgr(PP.getFileManager(), ModuleCache,
10236  PCHContainerRdr, PP.getHeaderSearchInfo()),
10237  DummyIdResolver(PP), ReadTimer(std::move(ReadTimer)), isysroot(isysroot),
10238  DisableValidationKind(DisableValidationKind),
10239  AllowASTWithCompilerErrors(AllowASTWithCompilerErrors),
10240  AllowConfigurationMismatch(AllowConfigurationMismatch),
10241  ValidateSystemInputs(ValidateSystemInputs),
10242  ValidateASTInputFilesContent(ValidateASTInputFilesContent),
10243  UseGlobalIndex(UseGlobalIndex), CurrSwitchCaseStmts(&SwitchCaseStmts) {
10244  SourceMgr.setExternalSLocEntrySource(this);
10245 
10246  for (const auto &Ext : Extensions) {
10247  auto BlockName = Ext->getExtensionMetadata().BlockName;
10248  auto Known = ModuleFileExtensions.find(BlockName);
10249  if (Known != ModuleFileExtensions.end()) {
10250  Diags.Report(diag::warn_duplicate_module_file_extension)
10251  << BlockName;
10252  continue;
10253  }
10254 
10255  ModuleFileExtensions.insert({BlockName, Ext});
10256  }
10257 }
10258 
10259 ASTReader::~ASTReader() {
10260  if (OwnsDeserializationListener)
10261  delete DeserializationListener;
10262 }
10263 
10264 IdentifierResolver &ASTReader::getIdResolver() {
10265  return SemaObj ? SemaObj->IdResolver : DummyIdResolver;
10266 }
10267 
10268 Expected<unsigned> ASTRecordReader::readRecord(llvm::BitstreamCursor &Cursor,
10269  unsigned AbbrevID) {
10270  Idx = 0;
10271  Record.clear();
10272  return Cursor.readRecord(AbbrevID, Record);
10273 }

10285 
10286 public:

10288  : Record(Record), Context(Record.getContext()) {}
10289 #define GEN_CLANG_CLAUSE_CLASS
10290 #define CLAUSE_CLASS(Enum, Str, Class) void Visit##Class(Class *C);
10291 #include "llvm/Frontend/OpenMP/OMP.inc"
10292  OMPClause *readClause();
10293  void VisitOMPClauseWithPreInit(OMPClauseWithPreInit *C);
10294  void VisitOMPClauseWithPostUpdate(OMPClauseWithPostUpdate *C);
10295 };

10303 OMPClause *OMPClauseReader::readClause() {
10304  OMPClause *C = nullptr;
10305  switch (llvm::omp::Clause(Record.readInt())) {
10306  case llvm::omp::OMPC_if:
10307  C = new (Context) OMPIfClause();
10308  break;
10309  case llvm::omp::OMPC_final:
10310  C = new (Context) OMPFinalClause();
10311  break;
10312  case llvm::omp::OMPC_num_threads:
10313  C = new (Context) OMPNumThreadsClause();
10314  break;
10315  case llvm::omp::OMPC_safelen:
10316  C = new (Context) OMPSafelenClause();
10317  break;
10318  case llvm::omp::OMPC_simdlen:
10319  C = new (Context) OMPSimdlenClause();
10320  break;
10321  case llvm::omp::OMPC_sizes: {
10322  unsigned NumSizes = Record.readInt();
10323  C = OMPSizesClause::CreateEmpty(Context, NumSizes);
10324  break;
10325  }
10326  case llvm::omp::OMPC_full:
10327  C = OMPFullClause::CreateEmpty(Context);
10328  break;
10329  case llvm::omp::OMPC_partial:
10330  C = OMPPartialClause::CreateEmpty(Context);
10331  break;
10332  case llvm::omp::OMPC_allocator:
10333  C = new (Context) OMPAllocatorClause();
10334  break;
10335  case llvm::omp::OMPC_collapse:
10336  C = new (Context) OMPCollapseClause();
10337  break;
10338  case llvm::omp::OMPC_default:
10339  C = new (Context) OMPDefaultClause();
10340  break;
10341  case llvm::omp::OMPC_proc_bind:
10342  C = new (Context) OMPProcBindClause();
10343  break;
10344  case llvm::omp::OMPC_schedule:
10345  C = new (Context) OMPScheduleClause();
10346  break;
10347  case llvm::omp::OMPC_ordered:
10348  C = OMPOrderedClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10349  break;
10350  case llvm::omp::OMPC_nowait:
10351  C = new (Context) OMPNowaitClause();
10352  break;
10353  case llvm::omp::OMPC_untied:
10354  C = new (Context) OMPUntiedClause();
10355  break;
10356  case llvm::omp::OMPC_mergeable:
10357  C = new (Context) OMPMergeableClause();
10358  break;
10359  case llvm::omp::OMPC_read:
10360  C = new (Context) OMPReadClause();
10361  break;
10362  case llvm::omp::OMPC_write:
10363  C = new (Context) OMPWriteClause();
10364  break;
10365  case llvm::omp::OMPC_update:
10366  C = OMPUpdateClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10367  break;
10368  case llvm::omp::OMPC_capture:
10369  C = new (Context) OMPCaptureClause();
10370  break;
10371  case llvm::omp::OMPC_compare:
10372  C = new (Context) OMPCompareClause();
10373  break;
10374  case llvm::omp::OMPC_fail:
10375  C = new (Context) OMPFailClause();
10376  break;
10377  case llvm::omp::OMPC_seq_cst:
10378  C = new (Context) OMPSeqCstClause();
10379  break;
10380  case llvm::omp::OMPC_acq_rel:
10381  C = new (Context) OMPAcqRelClause();
10382  break;
10383  case llvm::omp::OMPC_acquire:
10384  C = new (Context) OMPAcquireClause();
10385  break;
10386  case llvm::omp::OMPC_release:
10387  C = new (Context) OMPReleaseClause();
10388  break;
10389  case llvm::omp::OMPC_relaxed:
10390  C = new (Context) OMPRelaxedClause();
10391  break;
10392  case llvm::omp::OMPC_weak:
10393  C = new (Context) OMPWeakClause();
10394  break;

10396  C = new (Context) OMPThreadsClause();
10397  break;

10399  C = new (Context) OMPSIMDClause();
10400  break;
10401  case llvm::omp::OMPC_nogroup:
10402  C = new (Context) OMPNogroupClause();
10403  break;

10405  C = new (Context) OMPUnifiedAddressClause();
10406  break;

10460  break;

10463  break;

10471  unsigned NumVars = Record.readInt();

10474  break;
10475  }

10477  C = new (Context) OMPDeviceClause();
10478  break;

10482  Sizes.NumUniqueDeclarations = Record.readInt();

10486  break;
10487  }

10489  C = new (Context) OMPNumTeamsClause();
10490  break;

10492  C = new (Context) OMPThreadLimitClause();
10493  break;

10495  C = new (Context) OMPPriorityClause();
10496  break;

10498  C = new (Context) OMPGrainsizeClause();
10499  break;

10505  break;

10507  C = new (Context) OMPDistScheduleClause();
10508  break;
10509  case llvm::omp::OMPC_defaultmap:
10510  C = new (Context) OMPDefaultmapClause();
10511  break;
10512  case llvm::omp::OMPC_to: {
10513  OMPMappableExprListSizeTy Sizes;
10514  Sizes.NumVars = Record.readInt();
10515  Sizes.NumUniqueDeclarations = Record.readInt();
10516  Sizes.NumComponentLists = Record.readInt();
10517  Sizes.NumComponents = Record.readInt();
10518  C = OMPToClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Sizes);
10519  break;
10520  }

10522  OMPMappableExprListSizeTy Sizes;
10523  Sizes.NumVars = Record.readInt();
10524  Sizes.NumUniqueDeclarations = Record.readInt();
10525  Sizes.NumComponentLists = Record.readInt();
10526  Sizes.NumComponents = Record.readInt();
10527  C = OMPFromClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Sizes);
10528  break;
10529  }

10531  OMPMappableExprListSizeTy Sizes;

10534  Sizes.NumComponentLists = Record.readInt();
10535  Sizes.NumComponents = Record.readInt();
10536  C = OMPUseDevicePtrClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Sizes);
10537  break;
10538  }

10540  OMPMappableExprListSizeTy Sizes;

10543  Sizes.NumComponentLists = Record.readInt();

10546  break;

10552  Sizes.NumComponentLists = Record.readInt();
10553  Sizes.NumComponents = Record.readInt();
10554  C = OMPIsDevicePtrClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Sizes);
10555  break;
10556  }
10557  case llvm::omp::OMPC_has_device_addr: {
10558  OMPMappableExprListSizeTy Sizes;
10559  Sizes.NumVars = Record.readInt();
10560  Sizes.NumUniqueDeclarations = Record.readInt();
10561  Sizes.NumComponentLists = Record.readInt();
10562  Sizes.NumComponents = Record.readInt();
10563  C = OMPHasDeviceAddrClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Sizes);
10564  break;
10565  }
10566  case llvm::omp::OMPC_allocate:
10567  C = OMPAllocateClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10568  break;
10569  case llvm::omp::OMPC_nontemporal:
10570  C = OMPNontemporalClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10571  break;
10572  case llvm::omp::OMPC_inclusive:
10573  C = OMPInclusiveClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10574  break;
10575  case llvm::omp::OMPC_exclusive:
10576  C = OMPExclusiveClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10577  break;

10579  C = new (Context) OMPOrderClause();
10580  break;
10581  case llvm::omp::OMPC_init:

10583  break;

10585  C = new (Context) OMPUseClause();
10586  break;

10588  C = new (Context) OMPDestroyClause();
10589  break;

10591  C = new (Context) OMPNovariantsClause();
10592  break;

10594  C = new (Context) OMPNocontextClause();
10595  break;
10596  case llvm::omp::OMPC_detach:
10597  C = new (Context) OMPDetachClause();
10598  break;
10599  case llvm::omp::OMPC_uses_allocators:
10600  C = OMPUsesAllocatorsClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10601  break;
10602  case llvm::omp::OMPC_affinity:
10603  C = OMPAffinityClause::CreateEmpty(Context, Record.readInt());
10604  break;
10605  case llvm::omp::OMPC_filter:
10606  C = new (Context) OMPFilterClause();
10607  break;
10608  case llvm::omp::OMPC_bind:
10609  C = OMPBindClause::CreateEmpty(Context);
10610  break;
10611  case llvm::omp::OMPC_align:
10612  C = new (Context) OMPAlignClause();
10613  break;
10614  case llvm::omp::OMPC_ompx_dyn_cgroup_mem:
10615  C = new (Context) OMPXDynCGroupMemClause();
10616  break;
10617  case llvm::omp::OMPC_doacross: {
10618  unsigned NumVars = Record.readInt();
10619  unsigned NumLoops = Record.readInt();
10620  C = OMPDoacrossClause::CreateEmpty(Context, NumVars, NumLoops);
10621  break;
10622  }
10623  case llvm::omp::OMPC_ompx_attribute:
10624  C = new (Context) OMPXAttributeClause();
10625  break;
10626  case llvm::omp::OMPC_ompx_bare:
10627  C = new (Context) OMPXBareClause();
10628  break;
10629 #define OMP_CLAUSE_NO_CLASS(Enum, Str) \
10630  case llvm::omp::Enum: \
10631  break;
10632 #include "llvm/Frontend/OpenMP/OMPKinds.def"
10633  default:
10634  break;
10635  }
10636  assert(C && "Unknown OMPClause type");
10637 
10638  Visit(C);
10639  C->setLocStart(Record.readSourceLocation());
10640  C->setLocEnd(Record.readSourceLocation());
10641 
10642  return C;
10643 }

10721 void OMPClauseReader::VisitOMPScheduleClause(OMPScheduleClause *C) {

10947 void OMPClauseReader::VisitOMPReductionClause(OMPReductionClause *C) {
10948  VisitOMPClauseWithPostUpdate(C);
10949  C->setLParenLoc(Record.readSourceLocation());
10950  C->setModifierLoc(Record.readSourceLocation());
10951  C->setColonLoc(Record.readSourceLocation());
10952  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNSL = Record.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc();
10953  DeclarationNameInfo DNI = Record.readDeclarationNameInfo();
10954  C->setQualifierLoc(NNSL);
10955  C->setNameInfo(DNI);
10956 
10957  unsigned NumVars = C->varlist_size();
10958  SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
10959  Vars.reserve(NumVars);
10960  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10961  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10962  C->setVarRefs(Vars);
10963  Vars.clear();
10964  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10965  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10966  C->setPrivates(Vars);
10967  Vars.clear();
10968  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10969  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10970  C->setLHSExprs(Vars);
10971  Vars.clear();
10972  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10973  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10974  C->setRHSExprs(Vars);
10975  Vars.clear();
10976  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10977  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10978  C->setReductionOps(Vars);
10979  if (C->getModifier() == OMPC_REDUCTION_inscan) {
10980  Vars.clear();
10981  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10982  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10983  C->setInscanCopyOps(Vars);
10984  Vars.clear();
10985  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10986  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10987  C->setInscanCopyArrayTemps(Vars);
10988  Vars.clear();
10989  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
10990  Vars.push_back(Record.readSubExpr());
10991  C->setInscanCopyArrayElems(Vars);
10992  }
10993 }

11198 void OMPClauseReader::VisitOMPMapClause(OMPMapClause *C) {
11199  C->setLParenLoc(Record.readSourceLocation());
11200  bool HasIteratorModifier = false;
11201  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumberOfOMPMapClauseModifiers; ++I) {
11202  C->setMapTypeModifier(
11203  I, static_cast<OpenMPMapModifierKind>(Record.readInt()));
11204  C->setMapTypeModifierLoc(I, Record.readSourceLocation());
11205  if (C->getMapTypeModifier(I) == OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_iterator)
11206  HasIteratorModifier = true;
11207  }
11208  C->setMapperQualifierLoc(Record.readNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
11209  C->setMapperIdInfo(Record.readDeclarationNameInfo());
11210  C->setMapType(
11211  static_cast<OpenMPMapClauseKind>(Record.readInt()));
11212  C->setMapLoc(Record.readSourceLocation());
11213  C->setColonLoc(Record.readSourceLocation());
11214  auto NumVars = C->varlist_size();
11215  auto UniqueDecls = C->getUniqueDeclarationsNum();
11216  auto TotalLists = C->getTotalComponentListNum();
11217  auto TotalComponents = C->getTotalComponentsNum();
11218 
11219  SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
11220  Vars.reserve(NumVars);
11221  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumVars; ++i)
11222  Vars.push_back(Record.readExpr());
11223  C->setVarRefs(Vars);
11224 
11225  SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UDMappers;
11226  UDMappers.reserve(NumVars);
11227  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumVars; ++I)

11243  ListsPerDecl.push_back(Record.readInt());
11244  C->setDeclNumLists(ListsPerDecl);
11245 
11246  SmallVector<unsigned, 32> ListSizes;
11247  ListSizes.reserve(TotalLists);
11248  for (unsigned i = 0; i < TotalLists; ++i)
11249  ListSizes.push_back(Record.readInt());

11253  Components.reserve(TotalComponents);
11254  for (unsigned i = 0; i < TotalComponents; ++i) {
11255  Expr *AssociatedExprPr = Record.readExpr();
11256  auto *AssociatedDecl = Record.readDeclAs<ValueDecl>();
11257  Components.emplace_back(AssociatedExprPr, AssociatedDecl,
11258  /*IsNonContiguous=*/false);

11739  C->setLocEnd(Record.readSourceLocation());
11740 }
11741 
11742 void OMPClauseReader::VisitOMPXBareClause(OMPXBareClause *C) {}
11743 
11744 OMPTraitInfo *ASTRecordReader::readOMPTraitInfo() {
11745  OMPTraitInfo &TI = getContext().getNewOMPTraitInfo();
11746  TI.Sets.resize(readUInt32());
11747  for (auto &Set : TI.Sets) {
11748  Set.Kind = readEnum<llvm::omp::TraitSet>();
11749  Set.Selectors.resize(readUInt32());
11750  for (auto &Selector : Set.Selectors) {
11751  Selector.Kind = readEnum<llvm::omp::TraitSelector>();
11752  Selector.ScoreOrCondition = nullptr;
11753  if (readBool())
11754  Selector.ScoreOrCondition = readExprRef();
11755  Selector.Properties.resize(readUInt32());
11756  for (auto &Property : Selector.Properties)
11757  Property.Kind = readEnum<llvm::omp::TraitProperty>();
11758  }
11759  }
11760  return &TI;
11761 }
11762 
11763 void ASTRecordReader::readOMPChildren(OMPChildren *Data) {
11764  if (!Data)
11765  return;
11766  if (Reader->ReadingKind == ASTReader::Read_Stmt) {
11767  // Skip NumClauses, NumChildren and HasAssociatedStmt fields.
11768  skipInts(3);
11769  }
11770  SmallVector<OMPClause *, 4> Clauses(Data->getNumClauses());
11771  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Data->getNumClauses(); I < E; ++I)
11772  Clauses[I] = readOMPClause();
11773  Data->setClauses(Clauses);
11774  if (Data->hasAssociatedStmt())
11775  Data->setAssociatedStmt(readStmt());
11776  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Data->getNumChildren(); I < E; ++I)
11777  Data->getChildren()[I] = readStmt();
11778 }
11779 
11780 OpenACCClause *ASTRecordReader::readOpenACCClause() {
11781  OpenACCClauseKind ClauseKind = readEnum<OpenACCClauseKind>();
11782  SourceLocation BeginLoc = readSourceLocation();
11783  SourceLocation EndLoc = readSourceLocation();
11784 
11785  switch (ClauseKind) {
11786  case OpenACCClauseKind::Default: {
11787  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
11788  OpenACCDefaultClauseKind DCK = readEnum<OpenACCDefaultClauseKind>();
11789  return OpenACCDefaultClause::Create(getContext(), DCK, BeginLoc, LParenLoc,
11790  EndLoc);
11791  }
11792  case OpenACCClauseKind::If: {
11793  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
11794  Expr *CondExpr = readSubExpr();
11795  return OpenACCIfClause::Create(getContext(), BeginLoc, LParenLoc, CondExpr,
11796  EndLoc);
11797  }
11798  case OpenACCClauseKind::Self: {
11799  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
11800  Expr *CondExpr = readBool() ? readSubExpr() : nullptr;
11801  return OpenACCSelfClause::Create(getContext(), BeginLoc, LParenLoc,
11802  CondExpr, EndLoc);
11803  }
11804  case OpenACCClauseKind::NumGangs: {
11805  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
11806  unsigned NumClauses = readInt();
11807  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *> IntExprs;
11808  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumClauses; ++I)
11809  IntExprs.push_back(readSubExpr());
11810  return OpenACCNumGangsClause::Create(getContext(), BeginLoc, LParenLoc,
11811  IntExprs, EndLoc);
11812  }
11813  case OpenACCClauseKind::NumWorkers: {
11814  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
11815  Expr *IntExpr = readSubExpr();
11816  return OpenACCNumWorkersClause::Create(getContext(), BeginLoc, LParenLoc,
11817  IntExpr, EndLoc);
11818  }
11819  case OpenACCClauseKind::VectorLength: {
11820  SourceLocation LParenLoc = readSourceLocation();
11821  Expr *IntExpr = readSubExpr();
11822  return OpenACCVectorLengthClause::Create(getContext(), BeginLoc, LParenLoc,
11823  IntExpr, EndLoc);
11824  }
11825  case OpenACCClauseKind::Finalize:
11826  case OpenACCClauseKind::IfPresent:
11827  case OpenACCClauseKind::Seq:
11828  case OpenACCClauseKind::Independent:
11829  case OpenACCClauseKind::Auto:
11830  case OpenACCClauseKind::Worker:
11831  case OpenACCClauseKind::Vector:
11832  case OpenACCClauseKind::NoHost:
11833  case OpenACCClauseKind::Copy:
11834  case OpenACCClauseKind::UseDevice:
11835  case OpenACCClauseKind::Attach:
11836  case OpenACCClauseKind::Delete:
11837  case OpenACCClauseKind::Detach:
11838  case OpenACCClauseKind::Device:
11839  case OpenACCClauseKind::DevicePtr:
11840  case OpenACCClauseKind::DeviceResident:
11841  case OpenACCClauseKind::FirstPrivate:
11842  case OpenACCClauseKind::Host:
11843  case OpenACCClauseKind::Link:
11844  case OpenACCClauseKind::NoCreate:
11845  case OpenACCClauseKind::Present:
11846  case OpenACCClauseKind::Private:
11847  case OpenACCClauseKind::CopyOut:
11848  case OpenACCClauseKind::CopyIn:
11849  case OpenACCClauseKind::Create:
11850  case OpenACCClauseKind::Reduction:
11851  case OpenACCClauseKind::Collapse:
11852  case OpenACCClauseKind::Bind:
11853  case OpenACCClauseKind::DeviceNum:
11854  case OpenACCClauseKind::DefaultAsync:
11855  case OpenACCClauseKind::DeviceType:
11856  case OpenACCClauseKind::DType:
11857  case OpenACCClauseKind::Async:
11858  case OpenACCClauseKind::Tile:
11859  case OpenACCClauseKind::Gang:
11860  case OpenACCClauseKind::Wait:
11861  case OpenACCClauseKind::Invalid:
11862  llvm_unreachable("Clause serialization not yet implemented");
11863  }
11864  llvm_unreachable("Invalid Clause Kind");
11865 }
11866 
11867 void ASTRecordReader::readOpenACCClauseList(
11868  MutableArrayRef<const OpenACCClause *> Clauses) {
11869  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Clauses.size(); ++I)
11870  Clauses[I] = readOpenACCClause();
11871 }
